82bool isCustomPropertyName(const String& propertyName)
83{
84 return propertyName.length() > 2 && propertyName.characterAt(0) == '-' && propertyName.characterAt(1) == '-';
85}
86
87static bool hasPrefix(const char* string, unsigned length, const char* prefix)
88{
89 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
90 if (!prefix[i])
91 return true;
92 if (string[i] != prefix[i])
93 return false;
94 }
95 return false;
96}
97
98template <typename CharacterType>
99static CSSPropertyID cssPropertyID(const CharacterType* propertyName, unsigned length)
100{
101 char buffer[maxCSSPropertyNameLength + 1 + 1]; // 1 to turn "apple"/"khtml" into "webkit", 1 for null character
102
103 for (unsigned i = 0; i != length; ++i) {
104 CharacterType c = propertyName[i];
105 if (!c || c >= 0x7F)
106 return CSSPropertyInvalid; // illegal character
107 buffer[i] = toASCIILower(c);
108 }
109 buffer[length] = '\0';
110
111 if (auto hashTableEntry = findProperty(buffer, length)) {
112 auto propertyID = static_cast<CSSPropertyID>(hashTableEntry->id);
113 // FIXME: Should take account for flags in settings().
114 if (isEnabledCSSProperty(propertyID))
115 return propertyID;
116 }
117 return CSSPropertyInvalid;
118}
119
120static bool isAppleLegacyCssValueKeyword(const char* valueKeyword, unsigned length)
121{
122 static const char applePrefix[] = "-apple-";
123 static const char appleSystemPrefix[] = "-apple-system";
124 static const char applePayPrefix[] = "-apple-pay";
125
126#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
127 static const char* appleWirelessPlaybackTargetActive = getValueName(CSSValueAppleWirelessPlaybackTargetActive);
128#endif
129
130 return hasPrefix(valueKeyword, length, applePrefix)
131 && !hasPrefix(valueKeyword, length, appleSystemPrefix)
132 && !hasPrefix(valueKeyword, length, applePayPrefix)
133#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
134 && !WTF::equal(reinterpret_cast<const LChar*>(valueKeyword), reinterpret_cast<const LChar*>(appleWirelessPlaybackTargetActive), length)
135#endif
136 ;
137}
138
139template <typename CharacterType>
140static CSSValueID cssValueKeywordID(const CharacterType* valueKeyword, unsigned length)
141{
142 char buffer[maxCSSValueKeywordLength + 1 + 1]; // 1 to turn "apple"/"khtml" into "webkit", 1 for null character
143
144 for (unsigned i = 0; i != length; ++i) {
145 CharacterType c = valueKeyword[i];
146 if (!c || c >= 0x7F)
147 return CSSValueInvalid; // illegal keyword.
148 buffer[i] = WTF::toASCIILower(c);
149 }
150 buffer[length] = '\0';
151
152 if (buffer[0] == '-') {
153 // If the prefix is -apple- or -khtml-, change it to -webkit-.
154 // This makes the string one character longer.
155 // On iOS we don't want to change values starting with -apple-system to -webkit-system.
156 // FIXME: Remove this mangling without breaking the web.
157 if (isAppleLegacyCssValueKeyword(buffer, length)) {
158 memmove(buffer + 7, buffer + 6, length + 1 - 6);
159 memcpy(buffer, "-webkit", 7);
160 ++length;
161 }
162 }
163
164 const Value* hashTableEntry = findValue(buffer, length);
165 return hashTableEntry ? static_cast<CSSValueID>(hashTableEntry->id) : CSSValueInvalid;
166}
167
168CSSValueID cssValueKeywordID(StringView string)
169{
170 unsigned length = string.length();
171 if (!length)
172 return CSSValueInvalid;
173 if (length > maxCSSValueKeywordLength)
174 return CSSValueInvalid;
175
176 return string.is8Bit() ? cssValueKeywordID(string.characters8(), length) : cssValueKeywordID(string.characters16(), length);
177}
178
179CSSPropertyID cssPropertyID(StringView string)
180{
181 unsigned length = string.length();
182
183 if (!length)
184 return CSSPropertyInvalid;
185 if (length > maxCSSPropertyNameLength)
186 return CSSPropertyInvalid;
187
188 return string.is8Bit() ? cssPropertyID(string.characters8(), length) : cssPropertyID(string.characters16(), length);
189}

194CSSPropertyParser::CSSPropertyParser(const CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, Vector<CSSProperty, 256>* parsedProperties, bool consumeWhitespace)
195 : m_range(range)
196 , m_context(context)
197 , m_parsedProperties(parsedProperties)
198{
199 if (consumeWhitespace)
200 m_range.consumeWhitespace();
201}
202
203void CSSPropertyParser::addProperty(CSSPropertyID property, CSSPropertyID currentShorthand, Ref<CSSValue>&& value, bool important, bool implicit)
204{
205 if (!isEnabledCSSProperty(property))
206 return;
207
208 int shorthandIndex = 0;
209 bool setFromShorthand = false;
210
211 if (currentShorthand) {
212 auto shorthands = matchingShorthandsForLonghand(property);
213 setFromShorthand = true;
214 if (shorthands.size() > 1)
215 shorthandIndex = indexOfShorthandForLonghand(currentShorthand, shorthands);
216 }
217
218 m_parsedProperties->append(CSSProperty(property, WTFMove(value), important, setFromShorthand, shorthandIndex, implicit));
219}
220
221void CSSPropertyParser::addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyID property, Ref<CSSValue>&& value, bool important)
222{
223 for (auto longhand : shorthandForProperty(property))
224 addProperty(longhand, property, value.copyRef(), important);
225}
226
227bool CSSPropertyParser::parseValue(CSSPropertyID propertyID, bool important, const CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, ParsedPropertyVector& parsedProperties, StyleRuleType ruleType)
228{
229 int parsedPropertiesSize = parsedProperties.size();
230
231 CSSPropertyParser parser(range, context, &parsedProperties);
232 bool parseSuccess;
233
234 if (ruleType == StyleRuleType::FontFace)
235 parseSuccess = parser.parseFontFaceDescriptor(propertyID);
236 else if (ruleType == StyleRuleType::CounterStyle)
237 parseSuccess = parser.parseCounterStyleDescriptor(propertyID, context);
238 else
239 parseSuccess = parser.parseValueStart(propertyID, important);
240
241 if (!parseSuccess)
242 parsedProperties.shrink(parsedPropertiesSize);
243
244 return parseSuccess;
245}
246
247static RefPtr<CSSValue> maybeConsumeCSSWideKeyword(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
248{
249 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = range;
250 CSSValueID valueID = rangeCopy.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id();
251 if (!rangeCopy.atEnd())
252 return nullptr;
253
254 RefPtr<CSSValue> value;
255 if (valueID == CSSValueInherit)
256 value = CSSValuePool::singleton().createInheritedValue();
257 else if (valueID == CSSValueInitial)
258 value = CSSValuePool::singleton().createExplicitInitialValue();
259 else if (valueID == CSSValueUnset)
260 value = CSSValuePool::singleton().createUnsetValue();
261 else if (valueID == CSSValueRevert)
262 value = CSSValuePool::singleton().createRevertValue();
263 else
264 return nullptr;
265
266 range = rangeCopy;
267 return value;
268}
269
270RefPtr<CSSValue> CSSPropertyParser::parseSingleValue(CSSPropertyID property, const CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
271{
272 CSSPropertyParser parser(range, context, nullptr);
273 if (auto value = maybeConsumeCSSWideKeyword(parser.m_range))
274 return value;
275
276 RefPtr<CSSValue> value = parser.parseSingleValue(property);
277 if (!value || !parser.m_range.atEnd())
278 return nullptr;
279 return value;
280}

283{
284 CSSPropertyParser parser(tokens, context, nullptr);
285 return parser.canParseTypedCustomPropertyValue(syntax);
286}

288RefPtr<CSSCustomPropertyValue> CSSPropertyParser::parseTypedCustomPropertyValue(const String& name, const String& syntax, const CSSParserTokenRange& tokens, const Style::BuilderState& builderState, const CSSParserContext& context)
289{
290 CSSPropertyParser parser(tokens, context, nullptr, false);
291 RefPtr<CSSCustomPropertyValue> value = parser.parseTypedCustomPropertyValue(name, syntax, builderState);
292 if (!value || !parser.m_range.atEnd())
293 return nullptr;
294 return value;
295}

302
303bool CSSPropertyParser::parseValueStart(CSSPropertyID propertyID, bool important)
304{
305 if (consumeCSSWideKeyword(propertyID, important))
306 return true;
307
308 CSSParserTokenRange originalRange = m_range;
309 bool isShorthand = isShorthandCSSProperty(propertyID);
310
311 if (isShorthand) {
312 // Variable references will fail to parse here and will fall out to the variable ref parser below.
313 if (parseShorthand(propertyID, important))
314 return true;
315 } else {
316 RefPtr<CSSValue> parsedValue = parseSingleValue(propertyID);
317 if (parsedValue && m_range.atEnd()) {
318 addProperty(propertyID, CSSPropertyInvalid, *parsedValue, important);
319 return true;
320 }
321 }
322
323 if (CSSVariableParser::containsValidVariableReferences(originalRange, m_context)) {
324 auto variable = CSSVariableReferenceValue::create(originalRange);
325 if (isShorthand)
326 addExpandedPropertyForValue(propertyID, CSSPendingSubstitutionValue::create(propertyID, WTFMove(variable), m_context.baseURL), important);
327 else
328 addProperty(propertyID, CSSPropertyInvalid, WTFMove(variable), important);
329 return true;
330 }
331
332 return false;
333}
334
335bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeCSSWideKeyword(CSSPropertyID propertyID, bool important)
336{
337 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = m_range;
338 auto value = maybeConsumeCSSWideKeyword(rangeCopy);
339 if (!value)
340 return false;
341
342 const StylePropertyShorthand& shorthand = shorthandForProperty(propertyID);
343 if (!shorthand.length()) {
344 if (CSSProperty::isDescriptorOnly(propertyID))
345 return false;
346 addProperty(propertyID, CSSPropertyInvalid, value.releaseNonNull(), important);
347 } else
348 addExpandedPropertyForValue(propertyID, value.releaseNonNull(), important);
349 m_range = rangeCopy;
350 return true;
351}
352
353bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeTransformOrigin(bool important)
354{
355 if (auto resultXY = consumeOneOrTwoValuedPositionCoordinates(m_range, m_context.mode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid)) {
356 m_range.consumeWhitespace();
357 bool atEnd = m_range.atEnd();
358 auto resultZ = consumeLength(m_range, m_context.mode, ValueRange::All);
359 bool hasZ = resultZ;
360 if (!hasZ && !atEnd)
361 return false;
362 addProperty(CSSPropertyTransformOriginX, CSSPropertyTransformOrigin, WTFMove(resultXY->x), important);
363 addProperty(CSSPropertyTransformOriginY, CSSPropertyTransformOrigin, WTFMove(resultXY->y), important);
364 addProperty(CSSPropertyTransformOriginZ, CSSPropertyTransformOrigin, resultZ ? resultZ.releaseNonNull() : CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(0, CSSUnitType::CSS_PX), important, !hasZ);
365
366 return true;
367 }
368 return false;
369}
370
371bool CSSPropertyParser::consumePerspectiveOrigin(bool important)
372{
373 if (auto result = consumePositionCoordinates(m_range, m_context.mode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, PositionSyntax::Position)) {
374 addProperty(CSSPropertyPerspectiveOriginX, CSSPropertyPerspectiveOrigin, WTFMove(result->x), important);
375 addProperty(CSSPropertyPerspectiveOriginY, CSSPropertyPerspectiveOrigin, WTFMove(result->y), important);
376 return true;
377 }
378 return false;
379}
380
381// Methods for consuming non-shorthand properties starts here.
382static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeDisplay(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
383{
384 // Parse single keyword values
385 auto singleKeyword = consumeIdent<
386 // <display-box>
387 CSSValueContents,
388 CSSValueNone,
389 // <display-internal>
390 CSSValueTableCaption,
391 CSSValueTableCell,
392 CSSValueTableColumnGroup,
393 CSSValueTableColumn,
394 CSSValueTableHeaderGroup,
395 CSSValueTableFooterGroup,
396 CSSValueTableRow,
397 CSSValueTableRowGroup,
398 // <display-legacy>
399 CSSValueInlineBlock,
400 CSSValueInlineFlex,
401 CSSValueInlineGrid,
402 CSSValueInlineTable,
403 // Prefixed values
404 CSSValueWebkitInlineBox,
405 CSSValueWebkitBox,
406 // No layout support for the full <display-listitem> syntax, so treat it as <display-legacy>
407 CSSValueListItem
408 >(range);
409
410 if (singleKeyword)
411 return singleKeyword;
412
413 // Empty value, stop parsing
414 if (range.atEnd())
415 return nullptr;
416
417 // Convert -webkit-flex/-webkit-inline-flex to flex/inline-flex
418 CSSValueID nextValueID = range.peek().id();
419 if (nextValueID == CSSValueWebkitInlineFlex || nextValueID == CSSValueWebkitFlex) {
420 consumeIdent(range);
421 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(
422 nextValueID == CSSValueWebkitInlineFlex ? CSSValueInlineFlex : CSSValueFlex);
423 }
424
425 // Parse [ <display-outside> || <display-inside> ]
426 std::optional<CSSValueID> parsedDisplayOutside;
427 std::optional<CSSValueID> parsedDisplayInside;
428 while (!range.atEnd()) {
429 auto nextValueID = range.peek().id();
430 switch (nextValueID) {
431 // <display-outside>
432 case CSSValueBlock:
433 case CSSValueInline:
434 if (parsedDisplayOutside)
435 return nullptr;
436 parsedDisplayOutside = nextValueID;
437 break;
438 // <display-inside>
439 case CSSValueFlex:
440 case CSSValueFlow:
441 case CSSValueFlowRoot:
442 case CSSValueGrid:
443 case CSSValueTable:
444 if (parsedDisplayInside)
445 return nullptr;
446 parsedDisplayInside = nextValueID;
447 break;
448 default:
449 return nullptr;
450 }
451 consumeIdent(range);
452 }
453
454 // Set defaults when one of the two values are unspecified
455 CSSValueID displayOutside = parsedDisplayOutside.value_or(CSSValueBlock);
456 CSSValueID displayInside = parsedDisplayInside.value_or(CSSValueFlow);
457
458 auto selectShortValue = [&]() -> CSSValueID {
459 if (displayOutside == CSSValueBlock) {
460 // Alias display: flow to display: block
461 return displayInside == CSSValueFlow ? CSSValueBlock : displayInside;
462 }
463
464 // Convert `display: inline <display-inside>` to the equivalent short value
465 switch (displayInside) {
466 case CSSValueFlex:
467 return CSSValueInlineFlex;
468 case CSSValueFlow:
469 return CSSValueInline;
470 case CSSValueFlowRoot:
471 return CSSValueInlineBlock;
472 case CSSValueGrid:
473 return CSSValueInlineGrid;
474 case CSSValueTable:
475 return CSSValueInlineTable;
476 default:
477 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
478 return CSSValueInline;
479 }
480 };
481
482 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(selectShortValue());
483}
484
485static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeWillChange(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
486{
487 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueAuto)
488 return consumeIdent(range);
489
490 RefPtr<CSSValueList> values = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
491 // Every comma-separated list of identifiers is a valid will-change value,
492 // unless the list includes an explicitly disallowed identifier.
493 while (true) {
494 if (range.peek().type() != IdentToken)
495 return nullptr;
496 CSSPropertyID propertyID = cssPropertyID(range.peek().value());
497 if (propertyID != CSSPropertyInvalid) {
498 // Now "all" is used by both CSSValue and CSSPropertyValue.
499 // Need to return nullptr when currentValue is CSSPropertyAll.
500 if (propertyID == CSSPropertyWillChange || propertyID == CSSPropertyAll)
501 return nullptr;
502 values->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(propertyID));
503 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
504 } else {
505 switch (range.peek().id()) {
506 case CSSValueNone:
507 case CSSValueAll:
508 case CSSValueAuto:
509 case CSSValueDefault:
510 case CSSValueInitial:
511 case CSSValueInherit:
512 return nullptr;
513 case CSSValueContents:
514 case CSSValueScrollPosition:
515 values->append(consumeIdent(range).releaseNonNull());
516 break;
517 default:
518 // Append properties we don't recognize, but that are legal, as strings.
519 values->append(consumeCustomIdent(range).releaseNonNull());
520 break;
521 }
522 }
523
524 if (range.atEnd())
525 break;
526 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(range))
527 return nullptr;
528 }
529
530 return values;
531}
532
533#if ENABLE(VARIATION_FONTS)
534static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeFontVariationTag(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
535{
536 if (range.peek().type() != StringToken)
537 return nullptr;
538
539 auto string = range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().value();
540
541 FontTag tag;
542 if (string.length() != tag.size())
543 return nullptr;
544 for (unsigned i = 0; i < tag.size(); ++i) {
545 // Limits the range of characters to 0x20-0x7E, following the tag name rules defiend in the OpenType specification.
546 UChar character = string[i];
547 if (character < 0x20 || character > 0x7E)
548 return nullptr;
549 tag[i] = character;
550 }
551
552 if (range.atEnd())
553 return nullptr;
554
555 auto tagValue = consumeNumberRaw(range);
556 if (!tagValue)
557 return nullptr;
558
559 return CSSFontVariationValue::create(tag, *tagValue);
560}
561
562static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeFontVariationSettings(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
563{
564 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNormal)
565 return consumeIdent(range);
566
567 auto settings = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
568 do {
569 RefPtr<CSSValue> variationValue = consumeFontVariationTag(range);
570 if (!variationValue)
571 return nullptr;
572 settings->append(variationValue.releaseNonNull());
573 } while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(range));
574
575 if (!settings->length())
576 return nullptr;
577
578 return settings;
579}
580#endif // ENABLE(VARIATION_FONTS)
581
582static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumePage(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
583{
584 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueAuto)
585 return consumeIdent(range);
586 return consumeCustomIdent(range);
587}
588
589static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeQuotes(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
590{
591 auto id = range.peek().id();
592 if (id == CSSValueNone || id == CSSValueAuto)
593 return consumeIdent(range);
594 RefPtr<CSSValueList> values = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
595 while (!range.atEnd()) {
596 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> parsedValue = consumeString(range);
597 if (!parsedValue)
598 return nullptr;
599 values->append(parsedValue.releaseNonNull());
600 }
601 if (values->length() && values->length() % 2 == 0)
602 return values;
603 return nullptr;
604}
605
606class FontVariantLigaturesParser {
607public:
608 FontVariantLigaturesParser()
609 : m_sawCommonLigaturesValue(false)
610 , m_sawDiscretionaryLigaturesValue(false)
611 , m_sawHistoricalLigaturesValue(false)
612 , m_sawContextualLigaturesValue(false)
613 , m_result(CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated())
614 {
615 }
616
617 enum class ParseResult {
618 ConsumedValue,
619 DisallowedValue,
620 UnknownValue
621 };
622
623 ParseResult consumeLigature(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
624 {
625 CSSValueID valueID = range.peek().id();
626 switch (valueID) {
627 case CSSValueNoCommonLigatures:
628 case CSSValueCommonLigatures:
629 if (m_sawCommonLigaturesValue)
630 return ParseResult::DisallowedValue;
631 m_sawCommonLigaturesValue = true;
632 break;
633 case CSSValueNoDiscretionaryLigatures:
634 case CSSValueDiscretionaryLigatures:
635 if (m_sawDiscretionaryLigaturesValue)
636 return ParseResult::DisallowedValue;
637 m_sawDiscretionaryLigaturesValue = true;
638 break;
639 case CSSValueNoHistoricalLigatures:
640 case CSSValueHistoricalLigatures:
641 if (m_sawHistoricalLigaturesValue)
642 return ParseResult::DisallowedValue;
643 m_sawHistoricalLigaturesValue = true;
644 break;
645 case CSSValueNoContextual:
646 case CSSValueContextual:
647 if (m_sawContextualLigaturesValue)
648 return ParseResult::DisallowedValue;
649 m_sawContextualLigaturesValue = true;
650 break;
651 default:
652 return ParseResult::UnknownValue;
653 }
654 m_result->append(consumeIdent(range).releaseNonNull());
655 return ParseResult::ConsumedValue;
656 }
657
658 RefPtr<CSSValue> finalizeValue()
659 {
660 if (!m_result->length())
661 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal);
662 return WTFMove(m_result);
663 }
664
665private:
666 bool m_sawCommonLigaturesValue;
667 bool m_sawDiscretionaryLigaturesValue;
668 bool m_sawHistoricalLigaturesValue;
669 bool m_sawContextualLigaturesValue;
670 RefPtr<CSSValueList> m_result;
671};
672
673static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeFontVariantLigatures(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
674{
675 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNormal || range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
676 return consumeIdent(range);
677
678 FontVariantLigaturesParser ligaturesParser;
679 do {
680 if (ligaturesParser.consumeLigature(range) !=
681 FontVariantLigaturesParser::ParseResult::ConsumedValue)
682 return nullptr;
683 } while (!range.atEnd());
684
685 return ligaturesParser.finalizeValue();
686}
687
688static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeFontVariantEastAsian(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
689{
690 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNormal)
691 return consumeIdent(range);
692
693 RefPtr<CSSValueList> values = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
694 std::optional<FontVariantEastAsianVariant> variant;
695 std::optional<FontVariantEastAsianWidth> width;
696 std::optional<FontVariantEastAsianRuby> ruby;
697
698 while (!range.atEnd()) {
699 if (range.peek().type() != IdentToken)
700 return nullptr;
701
702 auto id = range.peek().id();
703
704 switch (id) {
705 case CSSValueJis78:
706 if (variant)
707 return nullptr;
708 variant = FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Jis78;
709 break;
710 case CSSValueJis83:
711 if (variant)
712 return nullptr;
713 variant = FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Jis83;
714 break;
715 case CSSValueJis90:
716 if (variant)
717 return nullptr;
718 variant = FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Jis90;
719 break;
720 case CSSValueJis04:
721 if (variant)
722 return nullptr;
723 variant = FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Jis04;
724 break;
725 case CSSValueSimplified:
726 if (variant)
727 return nullptr;
728 variant = FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Simplified;
729 break;
730 case CSSValueTraditional:
731 if (variant)
732 return nullptr;
733 variant = FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Traditional;
734 break;
735 case CSSValueFullWidth:
736 if (width)
737 return nullptr;
738 width = FontVariantEastAsianWidth::Full;
739 break;
740 case CSSValueProportionalWidth:
741 if (width)
742 return nullptr;
743 width = FontVariantEastAsianWidth::Proportional;
744 break;
745 case CSSValueRuby:
746 if (ruby)
747 return nullptr;
748 ruby = FontVariantEastAsianRuby::Yes;
749 break;
750 default:
751 return nullptr;
752 }
753
754 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
755 }
756
757 switch (variant.value_or(FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Normal)) {
758 case FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Normal:
759 break;
760 case FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Jis78:
761 values->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueJis78));
762 break;
763 case FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Jis83:
764 values->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueJis83));
765 break;
766 case FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Jis90:
767 values->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueJis90));
768 break;
769 case FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Jis04:
770 values->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueJis04));
771 break;
772 case FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Simplified:
773 values->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueSimplified));
774 break;
775 case FontVariantEastAsianVariant::Traditional:
776 values->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueTraditional));
777 break;
778 }
779
780 switch (width.value_or(FontVariantEastAsianWidth::Normal)) {
781 case FontVariantEastAsianWidth::Normal:
782 break;
783 case FontVariantEastAsianWidth::Full:
784 values->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueFullWidth));
785 break;
786 case FontVariantEastAsianWidth::Proportional:
787 values->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueProportionalWidth));
788 break;
789 }
790
791 switch (ruby.value_or(FontVariantEastAsianRuby::Normal)) {
792 case FontVariantEastAsianRuby::Normal:
793 break;
794 case FontVariantEastAsianRuby::Yes:
795 values->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueRuby));
796 }
797
798 if (!values->length())
799 return nullptr;
800
801 return values;
802}

821class FontVariantNumericParser {
822public:
823 FontVariantNumericParser()
824 : m_sawNumericFigureValue(false)
825 , m_sawNumericSpacingValue(false)
826 , m_sawNumericFractionValue(false)
827 , m_sawOrdinalValue(false)
828 , m_sawSlashedZeroValue(false)
829 , m_result(CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated())
830 {
831 }
832
833 enum class ParseResult {
834 ConsumedValue,
835 DisallowedValue,
836 UnknownValue
837 };
838
839 ParseResult consumeNumeric(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
840 {
841 CSSValueID valueID = range.peek().id();
842 switch (valueID) {
843 case CSSValueLiningNums:
844 case CSSValueOldstyleNums:
845 if (m_sawNumericFigureValue)
846 return ParseResult::DisallowedValue;
847 m_sawNumericFigureValue = true;
848 break;
849 case CSSValueProportionalNums:
850 case CSSValueTabularNums:
851 if (m_sawNumericSpacingValue)
852 return ParseResult::DisallowedValue;
853 m_sawNumericSpacingValue = true;
854 break;
855 case CSSValueDiagonalFractions:
856 case CSSValueStackedFractions:
857 if (m_sawNumericFractionValue)
858 return ParseResult::DisallowedValue;
859 m_sawNumericFractionValue = true;
860 break;
861 case CSSValueOrdinal:
862 if (m_sawOrdinalValue)
863 return ParseResult::DisallowedValue;
864 m_sawOrdinalValue = true;
865 break;
866 case CSSValueSlashedZero:
867 if (m_sawSlashedZeroValue)
868 return ParseResult::DisallowedValue;
869 m_sawSlashedZeroValue = true;
870 break;
871 default:
872 return ParseResult::UnknownValue;
873 }
874 m_result->append(consumeIdent(range).releaseNonNull());
875 return ParseResult::ConsumedValue;
876 }
877
878 RefPtr<CSSValue> finalizeValue()
879 {
880 if (!m_result->length())
881 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal);
882 return WTFMove(m_result);
883 }
884
885
886private:
887 bool m_sawNumericFigureValue;
888 bool m_sawNumericSpacingValue;
889 bool m_sawNumericFractionValue;
890 bool m_sawOrdinalValue;
891 bool m_sawSlashedZeroValue;
892 RefPtr<CSSValueList> m_result;
893};
894
895static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeFontVariantNumeric(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
896{
897 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNormal)
898 return consumeIdent(range);
899
900 FontVariantNumericParser numericParser;
901 do {
902 if (numericParser.consumeNumeric(range) !=
903 FontVariantNumericParser::ParseResult::ConsumedValue)
904 return nullptr;
905 } while (!range.atEnd());
906
907 return numericParser.finalizeValue();
908}

956static RefPtr<CSSValueList> consumeFontFamilyDescriptor(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
957{
958 // FIXME-NEWPARSER: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=196381 For compatibility with the old parser, we have to make
959 // a list here, even though the list always contains only a single family name.
960 // Once the old parser is gone, we can delete this function, make the caller
961 // use consumeFamilyName instead, and then patch the @font-face code to
962 // not expect a list with a single name in it.
963 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
964 RefPtr<CSSValue> parsedValue = consumeFamilyName(range);
965 if (parsedValue)
966 list->append(parsedValue.releaseNonNull());
967
968 if (!range.atEnd() || !list->length())
969 return nullptr;
970
971 return list;
972}

974static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeFontSynthesis(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
975{
976 // none | [ weight || style || small-caps ]
977 CSSValueID id = range.peek().id();
978 if (id == CSSValueNone)
979 return consumeIdent(range);
980
981 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
982 while (true) {
983 auto ident = consumeIdent<CSSValueWeight, CSSValueStyle, CSSValueSmallCaps>(range);
984 if (!ident)
985 break;
986 if (list->hasValue(ident.get()))
987 return nullptr;
988 list->append(ident.releaseNonNull());
989 }
990
991 if (!list->length())
992 return nullptr;
993 return list;
994}

1056static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCounter(CSSParserTokenRange& range, int defaultValue)
1057{
1058 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
1059 return consumeIdent(range);
1060
1061 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1062 do {
1063 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> counterName = consumeCustomIdent(range);
1064 if (!counterName)
1065 return nullptr;
1066 int i = defaultValue;
1067 if (auto counterValue = consumeIntegerRaw(range))
1068 i = *counterValue;
1069 list->append(createPrimitiveValuePair(counterName.releaseNonNull(), CSSPrimitiveValue::create(i, CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce));
1070 } while (!range.atEnd());
1071 return list;

1079static RefPtr<CSSValueList> consumeSize(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
1080{
1081 RefPtr<CSSValueList> result = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1082
1083 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueAuto) {
1084 result->append(consumeIdent(range).releaseNonNull());
1085 return result;
1086 }
1087
1088 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> width = consumeLength(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::NonNegative)) {
1089 RefPtr<CSSValue> height = consumeLength(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
1090 result->append(width.releaseNonNull());
1091 if (height)
1092 result->append(height.releaseNonNull());
1093 return result;
1094 }
1095
1096 RefPtr<CSSValue> pageSize = consumePageSize(range);
1097 RefPtr<CSSValue> orientation = consumeIdent<CSSValuePortrait, CSSValueLandscape>(range);
1098 if (!pageSize)
1099 pageSize = consumePageSize(range);
1100
1101 if (!orientation && !pageSize)
1102 return nullptr;
1103 if (pageSize)
1104 result->append(pageSize.releaseNonNull());
1105 if (orientation)
1106 result->append(orientation.releaseNonNull());
1107 return result;
1108}

1110static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeTextIndent(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
1111{
1112 // [ <length> | <percentage> ] && hanging? && each-line?
1113 RefPtr<CSSValue> lengthOrPercentage;
1114 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> eachLine;
1115 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> hanging;
1116
1117 do {
1118 if (!lengthOrPercentage) {
1119 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> textIndent = consumeLengthOrPercent(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All, UnitlessQuirk::Allow)) {
1120 lengthOrPercentage = textIndent;
1121 continue;
1122 }
1123 }
1124
1125 CSSValueID id = range.peek().id();
1126 if (!eachLine && id == CSSValueEachLine) {
1127 eachLine = consumeIdent(range);
1128 continue;
1129 }
1130
1131 if (!hanging && id == CSSValueHanging) {
1132 hanging = consumeIdent(range);
1133 continue;
1134 }
1135
1136 return nullptr;
1137 } while (!range.atEnd());
1138
1139 if (!lengthOrPercentage)
1140 return nullptr;
1141
1142 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1143 list->append(*lengthOrPercentage);
1144 if (hanging)
1145 list->append(hanging.releaseNonNull());
1146 if (eachLine)
1147 list->append(eachLine.releaseNonNull());
1148
1149 return list;
1150}

1188static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeClipComponent(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)

1194
1195static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeClip(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
1196{
1197 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueAuto)
1198 return consumeIdent(range);
1199
1200 if (range.peek().functionId() != CSSValueRect)
1201 return nullptr;
1202
1203 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(range);
1204 // rect(t, r, b, l) || rect(t r b l)
1205 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> top = consumeClipComponent(args, cssParserMode);
1206 if (!top)
1207 return nullptr;
1208 bool needsComma = consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args);
1209 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> right = consumeClipComponent(args, cssParserMode);
1210 if (!right || (needsComma && !consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args)))
1211 return nullptr;
1212 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> bottom = consumeClipComponent(args, cssParserMode);
1213 if (!bottom || (needsComma && !consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args)))
1214 return nullptr;
1215 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> left = consumeClipComponent(args, cssParserMode);
1216 if (!left || !args.atEnd())
1217 return nullptr;
1218
1219 auto rect = Rect::create();
1220 rect->setLeft(left.releaseNonNull());
1221 rect->setTop(top.releaseNonNull());
1222 rect->setRight(right.releaseNonNull());
1223 rect->setBottom(bottom.releaseNonNull());
1224 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(WTFMove(rect));
1225}

1245 return list;
1246}

1338static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeTransitionProperty(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
1339{
1340 const CSSParserToken& token = range.peek();
1341 if (token.type() != IdentToken)
1342 return nullptr;
1343 if (token.id() == CSSValueNone)
1344 return consumeIdent(range);
1345

1347 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
1348 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(property);

1354static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeSteps(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
1355{
1356 // https://drafts.csswg.org/css-easing-1/#funcdef-step-easing-function-steps
1357
1358 ASSERT(range.peek().functionId() == CSSValueSteps);
1359 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = range;
1360 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(rangeCopy);
1361
1362 auto stepsValue = consumePositiveIntegerRaw(args);
1363 if (!stepsValue)
1364 return nullptr;
1365
1366 std::optional<StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition> stepPosition;
1367 if (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args)) {
1368 switch (args.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id()) {
1369 case CSSValueJumpStart:
1370 stepPosition = StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition::JumpStart;
1371 break;
1372
1373 case CSSValueJumpEnd:
1374 stepPosition = StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition::JumpEnd;
1375 break;
1376
1377 case CSSValueJumpNone:
1378 stepPosition = StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition::JumpNone;
1379 break;
1380
1381 case CSSValueJumpBoth:
1382 stepPosition = StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition::JumpBoth;
1383 break;
1384
1385 case CSSValueStart:
1386 stepPosition = StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition::Start;
1387 break;
1388
1389 case CSSValueEnd:
1390 stepPosition = StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition::End;
1391 break;
1392
1393 default:
1394 return nullptr;
1395 }
1396 }
1397
1398 if (!args.atEnd())
1399 return nullptr;
1400
1401 if (*stepsValue == 1 && stepPosition == StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition::JumpNone)
1402 return nullptr;
1403
1404 range = rangeCopy;
1405 return CSSStepsTimingFunctionValue::create(*stepsValue, stepPosition);
1406}
1407
1408static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCubicBezier(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
1409{
1410 ASSERT(range.peek().functionId() == CSSValueCubicBezier);
1411 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = range;
1412 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(rangeCopy);
1413
1414 auto x1 = consumeNumberRaw(args);
1415 if (!x1 || *x1 < 0 || *x1 > 1)
1416 return nullptr;
1417
1418 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
1419 return nullptr;
1420
1421 auto y1 = consumeNumberRaw(args);
1422 if (!y1)
1423 return nullptr;
1424
1425 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
1426 return nullptr;
1427
1428 auto x2 = consumeNumberRaw(args);
1429 if (!x2 || *x2 < 0 || *x2 > 1)
1430 return nullptr;
1431
1432 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
1433 return nullptr;
1434
1435 auto y2 = consumeNumberRaw(args);
1436 if (!y2)
1437 return nullptr;
1438
1439 if (!args.atEnd())
1440 return nullptr;
1441
1442 range = rangeCopy;
1443 return CSSCubicBezierTimingFunctionValue::create(*x1, *y1, *x2, *y2);
1444}
1445
1446static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeSpringFunction(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
1447{
1448 ASSERT(range.peek().functionId() == CSSValueSpring);
1449 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = range;
1450 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(rangeCopy);
1451
1452 // Mass must be greater than 0.
1453 auto mass = consumeNumberRaw(args);
1454 if (!mass || *mass <= 0)
1455 return nullptr;
1456
1457 // Stiffness must be greater than 0.
1458 auto stiffness = consumeNumberRaw(args);
1459 if (!stiffness || *stiffness <= 0)
1460 return nullptr;
1461
1462 // Damping coefficient must be greater than or equal to 0.
1463 auto damping = consumeNumberRaw(args);
1464 if (!damping || *damping < 0)
1465 return nullptr;
1466
1467 // Initial velocity may have any value.
1468 auto initialVelocity = consumeNumberRaw(args);
1469 if (!initialVelocity)
1470 return nullptr;
1471
1472 if (!args.atEnd())
1473 return nullptr;
1474
1475 range = rangeCopy;
1476
1477 return CSSSpringTimingFunctionValue::create(*mass, *stiffness, *damping, *initialVelocity);
1478}
1479
1480static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeAnimationTimingFunction(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
1481{
1482 switch (range.peek().id()) {
1483 case CSSValueLinear:
1484 case CSSValueEase:
1485 case CSSValueEaseIn:
1486 case CSSValueEaseOut:
1487 case CSSValueEaseInOut:
1488 return consumeIdent(range);
1489
1490 case CSSValueStepStart:
1491 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
1492 return CSSStepsTimingFunctionValue::create(1, StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition::Start);
1493
1494 case CSSValueStepEnd:
1495 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
1496 return CSSStepsTimingFunctionValue::create(1, StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition::End);
1497
1498 default:
1499 break;
1500 }
1501
1502 CSSValueID function = range.peek().functionId();
1503 if (function == CSSValueCubicBezier)
1504 return consumeCubicBezier(range);
1505 if (function == CSSValueSteps)
1506 return consumeSteps(range);
1507 if (context.springTimingFunctionEnabled && function == CSSValueSpring)
1508 return consumeSpringFunction(range);
1509 return nullptr;
1510}
1511
1512static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeAnimationValue(CSSPropertyID property, CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
1513{
1514 switch (property) {
1515 case CSSPropertyAnimationDelay:
1516 case CSSPropertyTransitionDelay:
1517 return consumeTime(range, context.mode, ValueRange::All, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid);
1518 case CSSPropertyAnimationDirection:
1519 return consumeIdent<CSSValueNormal, CSSValueAlternate, CSSValueReverse, CSSValueAlternateReverse>(range);
1520 case CSSPropertyAnimationDuration:
1521 case CSSPropertyTransitionDuration:
1522 return consumeTime(range, context.mode, ValueRange::NonNegative, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid);
1523 case CSSPropertyAnimationFillMode:
1524 return consumeIdent<CSSValueNone, CSSValueForwards, CSSValueBackwards, CSSValueBoth>(range);
1525 case CSSPropertyAnimationIterationCount:
1526 return consumeAnimationIterationCount(range);
1527 case CSSPropertyAnimationName:
1528 return consumeAnimationName(range);
1529 case CSSPropertyAnimationPlayState:
1530 return consumeIdent<CSSValueRunning, CSSValuePaused>(range);
1531 case CSSPropertyTransitionProperty:
1532 return consumeTransitionProperty(range);
1533 case CSSPropertyAnimationTimingFunction:
1534 case CSSPropertyTransitionTimingFunction:
1535 return consumeAnimationTimingFunction(range, context);
1536 default:
1537 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1538 return nullptr;
1539 }
1540}
1541
1542static bool isValidAnimationPropertyList(CSSPropertyID property, const CSSValueList& valueList)
1543{
1544 if (property != CSSPropertyTransitionProperty || valueList.length() < 2)
1545 return true;
1546 for (auto& value : valueList) {
1547 if (value->isPrimitiveValue() && downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value.get()).isValueID()
1548 && downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value.get()).valueID() == CSSValueNone)
1549 return false;
1550 }
1551 return true;
1552}
1553
1554static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeAnimationPropertyList(CSSPropertyID property, CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
1555{
1556 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list;
1557 RefPtr<CSSValue> singleton;
1558 do {
1559 RefPtr<CSSValue> currentValue = consumeAnimationValue(property, range, context);
1560 if (!currentValue)
1561 return nullptr;
1562
1563 if (singleton && !list) {
1564 list = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
1565 list->append(singleton.releaseNonNull());
1566 }
1567
1568 if (list)
1569 list->append(currentValue.releaseNonNull());
1570 else
1571 singleton = WTFMove(currentValue);
1572
1573 } while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(range));
1574
1575 if (list) {
1576 if (!isValidAnimationPropertyList(property, *list))
1577 return nullptr;
1578
1579 ASSERT(list->length());
1580 return list;
1581 }
1582
1583 return singleton;
1584}
1585
1586bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeAnimationShorthand(const StylePropertyShorthand& shorthand, bool important)
1587{
1588 const unsigned longhandCount = shorthand.length();
1589 RefPtr<CSSValueList> longhands[8];
1590 ASSERT(longhandCount <= 8);
1591 for (size_t i = 0; i < longhandCount; ++i)
1592 longhands[i] = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
1593
1594 do {
1595 bool parsedLonghand[8] = { false };
1596 do {
1597 bool foundProperty = false;
1598 for (size_t i = 0; i < longhandCount; ++i) {
1599 if (parsedLonghand[i])
1600 continue;
1601
1602 if (auto value = consumeAnimationValue(shorthand.properties()[i], m_range, m_context)) {
1603 parsedLonghand[i] = true;
1604 foundProperty = true;
1605 longhands[i]->append(*value);
1606 break;
1607 }
1608 }
1609 if (!foundProperty)
1610 return false;
1611 } while (!m_range.atEnd() && m_range.peek().type() != CommaToken);
1612
1613 // FIXME: This will make invalid longhands, see crbug.com/386459
1614 for (size_t i = 0; i < longhandCount; ++i) {
1615 if (!parsedLonghand[i])
1616 longhands[i]->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue());
1617 parsedLonghand[i] = false;
1618 }
1619 } while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(m_range));
1620
1621 for (size_t i = 0; i < longhandCount; ++i) {
1622 if (!isValidAnimationPropertyList(shorthand.properties()[i], *longhands[i]))
1623 return false;
1624 }
1625
1626 for (size_t i = 0; i < longhandCount; ++i)
1627 addProperty(shorthand.properties()[i], shorthand.id(), *longhands[i], important);
1628
1629 return m_range.atEnd();
1630}

1634 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueAuto)
1635 return consumeIdent(range);
1636 return consumeInteger(range);
1637}

1639static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeShadow(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, bool isBoxShadowProperty)
1640{
1641 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
1642 return consumeIdent(range);
1643

1645 do {
1646 if (auto shadowValue = consumeSingleShadow(range, context, isBoxShadowProperty, isBoxShadowProperty))

1654static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeTextDecorationLine(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
1655{
1656 CSSValueID id = range.peek().id();
1657 if (id == CSSValueNone)
1658 return consumeIdent(range);
1659
1660 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1661 while (true) {
1662#if ENABLE(LETTERPRESS)
1663 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> ident = consumeIdent<CSSValueBlink, CSSValueUnderline, CSSValueOverline, CSSValueLineThrough, CSSValueWebkitLetterpress>(range);
1664#else
1665 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> ident = consumeIdent<CSSValueBlink, CSSValueUnderline, CSSValueOverline, CSSValueLineThrough>(range);
1666#endif
1667 if (!ident)
1668 break;
1669 if (list->hasValue(ident.get()))
1670 return nullptr;
1671 list->append(ident.releaseNonNull());
1672 }
1673
1674 if (!list->length())
1675 return nullptr;
1676 return list;
1677}

1700static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeTextEmphasisStyle(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
1701{
1702 CSSValueID id = range.peek().id();
1703 if (id == CSSValueNone)
1704 return consumeIdent(range);
1705
1706 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> textEmphasisStyle = consumeString(range))
1707 return textEmphasisStyle;
1708
1709 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> fill = consumeIdent<CSSValueFilled, CSSValueOpen>(range);
1710 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> shape = consumeIdent<CSSValueDot, CSSValueCircle, CSSValueDoubleCircle, CSSValueTriangle, CSSValueSesame>(range);
1711 if (!fill)
1712 fill = consumeIdent<CSSValueFilled, CSSValueOpen>(range);
1713 if (fill && shape) {
1714 RefPtr<CSSValueList> parsedValues = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1715 parsedValues->append(fill.releaseNonNull());
1716 parsedValues->append(shape.releaseNonNull());
1717 return parsedValues;
1718 }
1719 if (fill)
1720 return fill;
1721 if (shape)
1722 return shape;
1723 return nullptr;
1724}

1763
1764static bool consumeTranslate3d(CSSParserTokenRange& args, CSSParserMode cssParserMode, RefPtr<CSSFunctionValue>& transformValue)
1765{
1766 unsigned numberOfArguments = 2;
1767 RefPtr<CSSValue> parsedValue;
1768 do {
1769 parsedValue = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All);
1770 if (!parsedValue)
1771 return false;
1772 transformValue->append(*parsedValue);
1773 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
1774 return false;
1775 } while (--numberOfArguments);
1776 parsedValue = consumeLength(args, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All);
1777 if (!parsedValue)
1778 return false;
1779 transformValue->append(*parsedValue);
1780 return true;
1781}
1782
1783static bool consumeNumbers(CSSParserTokenRange& args, RefPtr<CSSFunctionValue>& transformValue, unsigned numberOfArguments)
1784{
1785 do {
1786 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> parsedValue = consumeNumber(args, ValueRange::All);
1787 if (!parsedValue)
1788 return false;
1789 transformValue->append(parsedValue.releaseNonNull());
1790 if (--numberOfArguments && !consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
1791 return false;
1792 } while (numberOfArguments);
1793 return true;
1794}
1795
1796static bool consumePerspective(CSSParserTokenRange& args, CSSParserMode cssParserMode, RefPtr<CSSFunctionValue>& transformValue)
1797{
1798 if (auto parsedValue = consumeLength(args, cssParserMode, ValueRange::NonNegative)) {
1799 transformValue->append(parsedValue.releaseNonNull());
1800 return true;
1801 }
1802
1803 auto perspective = consumeNumberRaw(args);
1804 if (!perspective || *perspective < 0)
1805 return false;
1806 transformValue->append(CSSPrimitiveValue::create(*perspective, CSSUnitType::CSS_PX));
1807 return true;
1808}
1809
1810static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeTransformValue(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
1811{
1812 CSSValueID functionId = range.peek().functionId();
1813 if (functionId == CSSValueInvalid)
1814 return nullptr;
1815 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(range);
1816 if (args.atEnd())
1817 return nullptr;
1818
1819 RefPtr<CSSFunctionValue> transformValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(functionId);
1820 RefPtr<CSSValue> parsedValue;
1821 switch (functionId) {
1822 case CSSValueRotate:
1823 case CSSValueRotateX:
1824 case CSSValueRotateY:
1825 case CSSValueRotateZ:
1826 case CSSValueSkewX:
1827 case CSSValueSkewY:
1828 case CSSValueSkew:
1829 parsedValue = consumeAngle(args, cssParserMode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, UnitlessZeroQuirk::Allow);
1830 if (!parsedValue)
1831 return nullptr;
1832 if (functionId == CSSValueSkew && consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args)) {
1833 transformValue->append(*parsedValue);
1834 parsedValue = consumeAngle(args, cssParserMode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, UnitlessZeroQuirk::Allow);
1835 if (!parsedValue)
1836 return nullptr;
1837 }
1838 break;
1839 case CSSValueScaleX:
1840 case CSSValueScaleY:
1841 case CSSValueScaleZ:
1842 case CSSValueScale:
1843 parsedValue = consumeNumber(args, ValueRange::All);
1844 if (!parsedValue)
1845 return nullptr;
1846 if (functionId == CSSValueScale && consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args)) {
1847 transformValue->append(*parsedValue);
1848 parsedValue = consumeNumber(args, ValueRange::All);
1849 if (!parsedValue)
1850 return nullptr;
1851 }
1852 break;
1853 case CSSValuePerspective:
1854 if (!consumePerspective(args, cssParserMode, transformValue))
1855 return nullptr;
1856 break;
1857 case CSSValueTranslateX:
1858 case CSSValueTranslateY:
1859 case CSSValueTranslate:
1860 parsedValue = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All);
1861 if (!parsedValue)
1862 return nullptr;
1863 if (functionId == CSSValueTranslate && consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args)) {
1864 transformValue->append(*parsedValue);
1865 parsedValue = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All);
1866 if (!parsedValue)
1867 return nullptr;
1868 }
1869 break;
1870 case CSSValueTranslateZ:
1871 parsedValue = consumeLength(args, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All);
1872 break;
1873 case CSSValueMatrix:
1874 case CSSValueMatrix3d:
1875 if (!consumeNumbers(args, transformValue, (functionId == CSSValueMatrix3d) ? 16 : 6))
1876 return nullptr;
1877 break;
1878 case CSSValueScale3d:
1879 if (!consumeNumbers(args, transformValue, 3))
1880 return nullptr;
1881 break;
1882 case CSSValueRotate3d:
1883 if (!consumeNumbers(args, transformValue, 3) || !consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
1884 return nullptr;
1885 parsedValue = consumeAngle(args, cssParserMode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, UnitlessZeroQuirk::Allow);
1886 if (!parsedValue)
1887 return nullptr;
1888 break;
1889 case CSSValueTranslate3d:
1890 if (!consumeTranslate3d(args, cssParserMode, transformValue))
1891 return nullptr;
1892 break;
1893 default:
1894 return nullptr;
1895 }
1896 if (parsedValue)
1897 transformValue->append(*parsedValue);
1898 if (!args.atEnd())
1899 return nullptr;
1900 return transformValue;
1901}
1902
1903static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeTransform(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
1904{
1905 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
1906 return consumeIdent(range);
1907
1908 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1909 do {
1910 RefPtr<CSSValue> parsedTransformValue = consumeTransformValue(range, cssParserMode);
1911 if (!parsedTransformValue)
1912 return nullptr;
1913 list->append(parsedTransformValue.releaseNonNull());
1914 } while (!range.atEnd());
1915
1916 return list;
1917}
1918
1919static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeTranslate(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
1920{
1921 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
1922 return consumeIdent(range);
1923
1924 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1925
1926 // https://drafts.csswg.org/css-transforms-2/#propdef-translate
1927 //
1928 // The translate property accepts 1-3 values, each specifying a translation against one axis, in the order X, Y, then Z.
1929 // If only one or two values are given, this specifies a 2d translation, equivalent to the translate() function. If the second
1930 // value is missing, it defaults to 0px. If three values are given, this specifies a 3d translation, equivalent to the
1931 // translate3d() function.
1932
1933 RefPtr<CSSValue> x = consumeLengthOrPercent(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All);
1934 if (!x)
1935 return list;
1936
1937 // If we got this far we have a valid x value, so we can directly add it to the list.
1938 list->append(*x);
1939
1940 range.consumeWhitespace();
1941 RefPtr<CSSValue> y = consumeLengthOrPercent(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All);
1942 if (!y)
1943 return list;
1944
1945 // If we have a calc() or non-zero y value, we can directly add it to the list. We only
1946 // want to add a zero y value if a non-zero z value is specified.
1947 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(y)) {
1948 auto& yPrimitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*y);
1949 if (yPrimitiveValue.isCalculated() || !*yPrimitiveValue.isZero())
1950 list->append(*y);
1951 }
1952
1953 range.consumeWhitespace();
1954 RefPtr<CSSValue> z = consumeLength(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All);
1955
1956 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(z)) {
1957 auto& zPrimitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*z);
1958 // If the z value is a zero value, we have nothing left to add to the list.
1959 if (!zPrimitiveValue.isCalculated() && *zPrimitiveValue.isZero())
1960 return list;
1961 // Add the zero value for y if we did not already add a y value.
1962 if (list->length() == 1)
1963 list->append(CSSPrimitiveValue::create(0, CSSUnitType::CSS_PX));
1964 list->append(*z);
1965 }
1966
1967 return list;
1968}
1969
1970static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeScale(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode)
1971{
1972 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
1973 return consumeIdent(range);
1974
1975 // https://www.w3.org/TR/css-transforms-2/#propdef-scale
1976 //
1977 // The scale property accepts 1-3 values, each specifying a scale along one axis, in order X, Y, then Z.
1978 //
1979 // If only the X value is given, the Y value defaults to the same value.
1980 //
1981 // If one or two values are given, this specifies a 2d scaling, equivalent to the scale() function.
1982 // If three values are given, this specifies a 3d scaling, equivalent to the scale3d() function.
1983
1984 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1985
1986 RefPtr<CSSValue> x = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::All);
1987 if (!x)
1988 return list;
1989 list->append(*x);
1990 range.consumeWhitespace();
1991
1992 RefPtr<CSSValue> y = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::All);
1993 if (!y)
1994 return list;
1995
1996 // If the x and y values are the same, the y value is not needed.
1997 if (downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*x).floatValue() != downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*y).floatValue())
1998 list->append(*y);
1999 range.consumeWhitespace();
2000
2001 RefPtr<CSSValue> z = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::All);
2002 if (!z)
2003 return list;
2004 if (downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*z).floatValue() != 1.0) {
2005 // We only need to append the z value if it's set to something other than 1.
2006 // In case y was not added yet, because it was equal to x, we must append it
2007 // prior to appending z.
2008 if (list->length() == 1)
2009 list->append(*y);
2010 list->append(*z);
2011 }
2012
2013 return list;
2014}
2015
2016static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeRotate(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
2017{
2018 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
2019 return consumeIdent(range);
2020
2021 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
2022
2023 // https://www.w3.org/TR/css-transforms-2/#propdef-rotate
2024 //
2025 // The rotate property accepts an angle to rotate an element, and optionally an axis to rotate it around.
2026 //
2027 // If the axis is omitted, this specifies a 2d rotation, equivalent to the rotate() function.
2028 //
2029 // Otherwise, it specifies a 3d rotation: if x, y, or z is given, it specifies a rotation around that axis,
2030 // equivalent to the rotateX()/etc 3d transform functions. Alternately, the axis can be specified explicitly
2031 // by giving three numbers representing the x, y, and z components of an origin-centered vector, equivalent
2032 // to the rotate3d() function.
2033
2034 RefPtr<CSSValue> angle;
2035 RefPtr<CSSValue> axisIdentifier;
2036
2037 while (!range.atEnd()) {
2038 // First, attempt to parse a number, which might be in a series of 3 specifying the rotation axis.
2039 RefPtr<CSSValue> parsedValue = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::All);
2040 if (parsedValue) {
2041 // If we've encountered an axis identifier, then this valus is invalid.
2042 if (axisIdentifier)
2043 return nullptr;
2044 list->append(*parsedValue);
2045 range.consumeWhitespace();
2046 continue;
2047 }
2048
2049 // Then, attempt to parse an angle. We try this as a fallback rather than the first option because
2050 // a unitless 0 angle would be consumed as an angle.
2051 parsedValue = consumeAngle(range, cssParserMode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, UnitlessZeroQuirk::Allow);
2052 if (parsedValue) {
2053 // If we had already parsed an angle or numbers but not 3 in a row, this value is invalid.
2054 if (angle || (list->length() && list->length() != 3))
2055 return nullptr;
2056 angle = parsedValue;
2057 range.consumeWhitespace();
2058 continue;
2059 }
2060
2061 // Finally, attempt to parse one of the axis identifiers.
2062 parsedValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueX, CSSValueY, CSSValueZ>(range);
2063 // If we failed to find one of those identifiers or one was already specified, or we'd previously
2064 // encountered numbers to specify a rotation axis, then this value is invalid.
2065 if (!parsedValue || axisIdentifier || list->length())
2066 return nullptr;
2067 axisIdentifier = parsedValue;
2068 range.consumeWhitespace();
2069 }
2070
2071 // We must have an angle to have a valid value.
2072 if (!angle)
2073 return nullptr;
2074
2075 if (list->length() == 3) {
2076 // The first valid case is if we have 3 items in the list, meaning we parsed three consecutive number values
2077 // to specify the rotation axis. In that case, we must not also have encountered an axis identifier.
2078 ASSERT(!axisIdentifier);
2079
2080 // No we must check the values since if we have a vector in the x, y or z axis alone we must serialize to the
2081 // matching identifier.
2082 auto x = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*list->itemWithoutBoundsCheck(0)).doubleValue();
2083 auto y = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*list->itemWithoutBoundsCheck(1)).doubleValue();
2084 auto z = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*list->itemWithoutBoundsCheck(2)).doubleValue();
2085
2086 if (x && !y && !z) {
2087 list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
2088 list->append(CSSPrimitiveValue::createIdentifier(CSSValueX));
2089 } else if (!x && y && !z) {
2090 list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
2091 list->append(CSSPrimitiveValue::createIdentifier(CSSValueY));
2092 } else if (!x && !y && z)
2093 list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
2094
2095 // Finally, we must append the angle.
2096 list->append(*angle);
2097 } else if (!list->length()) {
2098 // The second valid case is if we have no item in the list, meaning we have either an optional rotation axis
2099 // using an identifier. In that case, we must add the axis identifier is specified and then add the angle.
2100 if (is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(axisIdentifier) && downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*axisIdentifier).valueID() != CSSValueZ)
2101 list->append(*axisIdentifier);
2102 list->append(*angle);
2103 } else
2104 return nullptr;
2105
2106 return list;
2107}
2108
2109template <CSSValueID start, CSSValueID end>
2110static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumePositionLonghand(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
2111{
2112 if (range.peek().type() == IdentToken) {
2113 CSSValueID id = range.peek().id();
2114 int percent;
2115 if (id == start)
2116 percent = 0;
2117 else if (id == CSSValueCenter)
2118 percent = 50;
2119 else if (id == end)
2120 percent = 100;
2121 else
2122 return nullptr;
2123 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
2124 return CSSPrimitiveValue::create(percent, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE);
2125 }
2126 return consumeLengthOrPercent(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All);
2127}

2171
2172static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumePaintOrder(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
2173{
2174 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNormal)
2175 return consumeIdent(range);
2176
2177 Vector<CSSValueID, 3> paintTypeList;
2178 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> fill;
2179 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> stroke;
2180 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> markers;
2181 do {
2182 CSSValueID id = range.peek().id();
2183 if (id == CSSValueFill && !fill)
2184 fill = consumeIdent(range);
2185 else if (id == CSSValueStroke && !stroke)
2186 stroke = consumeIdent(range);
2187 else if (id == CSSValueMarkers && !markers)
2188 markers = consumeIdent(range);
2189 else
2190 return nullptr;
2191 paintTypeList.append(id);
2192 } while (!range.atEnd());
2193
2194 // After parsing we serialize the paint-order list. Since it is not possible to
2195 // pop a last list items from CSSValueList without bigger cost, we create the
2196 // list after parsing.
2197 CSSValueID firstPaintOrderType = paintTypeList.at(0);
2198 RefPtr<CSSValueList> paintOrderList = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
2199 switch (firstPaintOrderType) {
2200 case CSSValueFill:
2201 case CSSValueStroke:
2202 paintOrderList->append(firstPaintOrderType == CSSValueFill ? fill.releaseNonNull() : stroke.releaseNonNull());
2203 if (paintTypeList.size() > 1) {
2204 if (paintTypeList.at(1) == CSSValueMarkers)
2205 paintOrderList->append(markers.releaseNonNull());
2206 }
2207 break;
2208 case CSSValueMarkers:
2209 paintOrderList->append(markers.releaseNonNull());
2210 if (paintTypeList.size() > 1) {
2211 if (paintTypeList.at(1) == CSSValueStroke)
2212 paintOrderList->append(stroke.releaseNonNull());
2213 }
2214 break;
2215 default:
2216 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2217 }
2218
2219 return paintOrderList;
2220}

2276static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCursor(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, bool inQuirksMode)
2277{
2278 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list;
2279 while (auto image = consumeImage(range, context, { AllowedImageType::URLFunction, AllowedImageType::ImageSet })) {
2280 std::optional<IntPoint> hotSpot;
2281 if (auto x = consumeNumberRaw(range)) {
2282 auto y = consumeNumberRaw(range);
2283 if (!y)
2284 return nullptr;
2285 // FIXME: Should we clamp or round instead of just casting from double to int?
2286 hotSpot = IntPoint { static_cast<int>(*x), static_cast<int>(*y) };
2287 }
2288
2289 if (!list)
2290 list = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
2291
2292 list->append(CSSCursorImageValue::create(image.releaseNonNull(), hotSpot, context.isContentOpaque ? LoadedFromOpaqueSource::Yes : LoadedFromOpaqueSource::No));
2293 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(range))
2294 return nullptr;
2295 }
2296
2297 CSSValueID id = range.peek().id();
2298 RefPtr<CSSValue> cursorType;
2299 if (id == CSSValueHand) {
2300 if (!inQuirksMode) // Non-standard behavior
2301 return nullptr;
2302 cursorType = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValuePointer);
2303 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
2304 } else if ((id >= CSSValueAuto && id <= CSSValueWebkitZoomOut) || id == CSSValueCopy || id == CSSValueNone) {
2305 cursorType = consumeIdent(range);
2306 } else {
2307 return nullptr;
2308 }
2309
2310 if (!list)
2311 return cursorType;
2312 list->append(cursorType.releaseNonNull());
2313 return list;
2314}

2316static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeAttr(CSSParserTokenRange args, CSSParserContext context)
2317{
2318 if (args.peek().type() != IdentToken)
2319 return nullptr;
2320
2321 CSSParserToken token = args.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
2322 AtomString attrName;
2323 if (context.isHTMLDocument)
2324 attrName = token.value().convertToASCIILowercaseAtom();
2325 else
2326 attrName = token.value().toAtomString();
2327
2328 if (!args.atEnd())
2329 return nullptr;
2330
2331 // FIXME: Consider moving to a CSSFunctionValue with a custom-ident rather than a special CSS_ATTR primitive value.
2332 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(attrName, CSSUnitType::CSS_ATTR);
2333}

2335static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCounterContent(CSSParserTokenRange args, bool counters)
2336{
2337 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> identifier = consumeCustomIdent(args);
2338 if (!identifier)
2339 return nullptr;
2340
2341 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> separator;
2342 if (!counters)
2343 separator = CSSPrimitiveValue::create(String(), CSSUnitType::CSS_STRING);
2344 else {
2345 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args) || args.peek().type() != StringToken)
2346 return nullptr;
2347 separator = CSSPrimitiveValue::create(args.consumeIncludingWhitespace().value().toString(), CSSUnitType::CSS_STRING);
2348 }
2349
2350 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> listStyle;
2351 if (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args)) {
2352 CSSValueID id = args.peek().id();
2353 if ((id != CSSValueNone && !isPredefinedCounterStyle(id)))
2354 return nullptr;
2355 listStyle = consumeIdent(args);
2356 } else
2357 listStyle = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueDecimal);
2358
2359 if (!args.atEnd())
2360 return nullptr;
2361
2362 // FIXME-NEWPARSER: Should just have a CSSCounterValue.
2363 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(Counter::create(identifier.releaseNonNull(), listStyle.releaseNonNull(), separator.releaseNonNull()));
2364}

2366static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeContent(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserContext context)
2367{
2368 if (identMatches<CSSValueNone, CSSValueNormal>(range.peek().id()))
2369 return consumeIdent(range);
2370
2371 RefPtr<CSSValueList> values = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
2372
2373 do {
2374 RefPtr<CSSValue> parsedValue = consumeImage(range, context);
2375 if (!parsedValue)
2376 parsedValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueOpenQuote, CSSValueCloseQuote, CSSValueNoOpenQuote, CSSValueNoCloseQuote>(range);
2377 if (!parsedValue)
2378 parsedValue = consumeString(range);
2379 if (!parsedValue) {
2380 if (range.peek().functionId() == CSSValueAttr)
2381 parsedValue = consumeAttr(consumeFunction(range), context);
2382 else if (range.peek().functionId() == CSSValueCounter)
2383 parsedValue = consumeCounterContent(consumeFunction(range), false);
2384 else if (range.peek().functionId() == CSSValueCounters)
2385 parsedValue = consumeCounterContent(consumeFunction(range), true);
2386 if (!parsedValue)
2387 return nullptr;
2388 }
2389 values->append(parsedValue.releaseNonNull());
2390 } while (!range.atEnd());
2391
2392 return values;
2393}

2395static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumePerspective(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
2396{
2397 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
2398 return consumeIdent(range);
2399
2400 if (auto parsedValue = consumeLength(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::All)) {
2401 if (!parsedValue->isNegative().value_or(false))
2402 return parsedValue;
2403 return nullptr;
2404 }
2405
2406 // FIXME: Make this quirk only apply to the webkit prefixed version of the property.
2407 auto perspective = consumeNumberRaw(range);
2408 if (!perspective || *perspective < 0)
2409 return nullptr;
2410 return CSSPrimitiveValue::create(*perspective, CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
2411}

2413static RefPtr<CSSValueList> consumeScrollSnapAlign(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
2414{
2415 auto firstValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueNone, CSSValueStart, CSSValueCenter, CSSValueEnd>(range);
2416 if (!firstValue)
2417 return nullptr;
2418
2419 auto secondValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueNone, CSSValueStart, CSSValueCenter, CSSValueEnd>(range);
2420 bool shouldAddSecondValue = secondValue && !secondValue->equals(*firstValue);
2421
2422 RefPtr<CSSValueList> alignmentValue = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
2423 alignmentValue->append(firstValue.releaseNonNull());
2424
2425 // Only add the second value if it differs from the first so that we produce the canonical
2426 // serialization of this CSSValueList.
2427 if (shouldAddSecondValue)
2428 alignmentValue->append(secondValue.releaseNonNull());
2429
2430 return alignmentValue;
2431}

2433static RefPtr<CSSValueList> consumeScrollSnapType(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
2434{
2435 RefPtr<CSSValueList> typeValue = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
2436
2437 auto firstValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueNone, CSSValueX, CSSValueY, CSSValueBlock, CSSValueInline, CSSValueBoth>(range);
2438 if (!firstValue)
2439 return nullptr;
2440 typeValue->append(firstValue.releaseNonNull());
2441
2442 // We only add the second value if it is not the initial value as described in specification
2443 // so that serialization of this CSSValueList produces the canonical serialization.
2444 auto secondValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueProximity, CSSValueMandatory>(range);
2445 if (secondValue && secondValue->valueID() != CSSValueProximity)
2446 typeValue->append(secondValue.releaseNonNull());
2447
2448 return typeValue;

2589static void complete4Sides(RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> side[4])
2590{
2591 if (side[3])
2592 return;
2593 if (!side[2]) {
2594 if (!side[1])
2595 side[1] = side[0];
2596 side[2] = side[0];
2597 }
2598 side[3] = side[1];
2599}
2600
2601static bool consumeRadii(RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> horizontalRadii[4], RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> verticalRadii[4], CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode, bool useLegacyParsing)
2602{
2603 unsigned i = 0;
2604 for (; i < 4 && !range.atEnd() && range.peek().type() != DelimiterToken; ++i) {
2605 horizontalRadii[i] = consumeLengthOrPercent(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2606 if (!horizontalRadii[i])
2607 return false;
2608 }
2609 if (!horizontalRadii[0])
2610 return false;
2611 if (range.atEnd()) {
2612 // Legacy syntax: -webkit-border-radius: l1 l2; is equivalent to border-radius: l1 / l2;
2613 if (useLegacyParsing && i == 2) {
2614 verticalRadii[0] = horizontalRadii[1];
2615 horizontalRadii[1] = nullptr;
2616 } else {
2617 complete4Sides(horizontalRadii);
2618 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
2619 verticalRadii[i] = horizontalRadii[i];
2620 return true;
2621 }
2622 } else {
2623 if (!consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(range))
2624 return false;
2625 for (i = 0; i < 4 && !range.atEnd(); ++i) {
2626 verticalRadii[i] = consumeLengthOrPercent(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2627 if (!verticalRadii[i])
2628 return false;
2629 }
2630 if (!verticalRadii[0] || !range.atEnd())
2631 return false;
2632 }
2633 complete4Sides(horizontalRadii);
2634 complete4Sides(verticalRadii);
2635 return true;
2636}
2637
2638static RefPtr<CSSBasicShapeInset> consumeBasicShapeInset(CSSParserTokenRange& args, const CSSParserContext& context)
2639{
2640 RefPtr<CSSBasicShapeInset> shape = CSSBasicShapeInset::create();
2641 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> top = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, context.mode, ValueRange::All);
2642 if (!top)
2643 return nullptr;
2644 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> right = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, context.mode, ValueRange::All);
2645 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> bottom;
2646 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> left;
2647 if (right) {
2648 bottom = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, context.mode, ValueRange::All);
2649 if (bottom)
2650 left = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, context.mode, ValueRange::All);
2651 }
2652 if (left)
2653 shape->updateShapeSize4Values(top.releaseNonNull(), right.releaseNonNull(), bottom.releaseNonNull(), left.releaseNonNull());
2654 else if (bottom)
2655 shape->updateShapeSize3Values(top.releaseNonNull(), right.releaseNonNull(), bottom.releaseNonNull());
2656 else if (right)
2657 shape->updateShapeSize2Values(top.releaseNonNull(), right.releaseNonNull());
2658 else
2659 shape->updateShapeSize1Value(top.releaseNonNull());
2660
2661 if (consumeIdent<CSSValueRound>(args)) {
2662 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> horizontalRadii[4] = { 0 };
2663 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> verticalRadii[4] = { 0 };
2664 if (!consumeRadii(horizontalRadii, verticalRadii, args, context.mode, false))
2665 return nullptr;
2666 shape->setTopLeftRadius(createPrimitiveValuePair(horizontalRadii[0].releaseNonNull(), verticalRadii[0].releaseNonNull(), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce));
2667 shape->setTopRightRadius(createPrimitiveValuePair(horizontalRadii[1].releaseNonNull(), verticalRadii[1].releaseNonNull(), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce));
2668 shape->setBottomRightRadius(createPrimitiveValuePair(horizontalRadii[2].releaseNonNull(), verticalRadii[2].releaseNonNull(), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce));
2669 shape->setBottomLeftRadius(createPrimitiveValuePair(horizontalRadii[3].releaseNonNull(), verticalRadii[3].releaseNonNull(), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce));
2670 }
2671 return shape;
2672}
2673
2674static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeBasicShape(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
2675{
2676 if (range.peek().type() != FunctionToken)
2677 return nullptr;
2678 CSSValueID id = range.peek().functionId();
2679 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = range;
2680 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(rangeCopy);
2681
2682 // FIXME-NEWPARSER: CSSBasicShape should be a CSSValue, and shapes should not be primitive values.
2683 RefPtr<CSSBasicShape> shape;
2684 if (id == CSSValueCircle)
2685 shape = consumeBasicShapeCircle(args, context);
2686 else if (id == CSSValueEllipse)
2687 shape = consumeBasicShapeEllipse(args, context);
2688 else if (id == CSSValuePolygon)
2689 shape = consumeBasicShapePolygon(args, context);
2690 else if (id == CSSValueInset)
2691 shape = consumeBasicShapeInset(args, context);
2692 else if (id == CSSValuePath)
2693 shape = consumeBasicShapePath(args);
2694 if (!shape)
2695 return nullptr;
2696 range = rangeCopy;
2697
2698 if (!args.atEnd())
2699 return nullptr;
2700
2701 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(shape.releaseNonNull());
2702}
2703
2704static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeBasicShapeOrBox(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
2705{
2706 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
2707 bool shapeFound = false;
2708 bool boxFound = false;
2709 while (!range.atEnd() && !(shapeFound && boxFound)) {
2710 RefPtr<CSSValue> componentValue;
2711 if (range.peek().type() == FunctionToken && !shapeFound) {
2712 componentValue = consumeBasicShape(range, context);
2713 shapeFound = true;
2714 } else if (range.peek().type() == IdentToken && !boxFound) {
2715 componentValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueContentBox, CSSValuePaddingBox, CSSValueBorderBox, CSSValueMarginBox, CSSValueFillBox, CSSValueStrokeBox, CSSValueViewBox>(range);
2716 boxFound = true;
2717 }
2718 if (!componentValue)
2719 return nullptr;
2720 list->append(componentValue.releaseNonNull());
2721 }
2722
2723 if (!range.atEnd() || !list->length())
2724 return nullptr;
2725
2726 return list;
2727}

2729static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeClipPath(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
2730{
2731 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
2732 return consumeIdent(range);
2733 if (RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> url = consumeUrl(range))
2734 return url;
2735 return consumeBasicShapeOrBox(range, context);
2736}
2737
2738static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeShapeOutside(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
2739{
2740 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> imageValue = consumeImageOrNone(range, context))
2741 return imageValue;
2742 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
2743 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> boxValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueContentBox, CSSValuePaddingBox, CSSValueBorderBox, CSSValueMarginBox>(range))
2744 list->append(boxValue.releaseNonNull());
2745 if (RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> shapeValue = consumeBasicShape(range, context)) {
2746 if (shapeValue->shapeValue()->type() == CSSBasicShapeCircle::CSSBasicShapePathType)
2747 return nullptr;
2748 list->append(shapeValue.releaseNonNull());
2749 if (list->length() < 2) {
2750 if (RefPtr<CSSValue> boxValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueContentBox, CSSValuePaddingBox, CSSValueBorderBox, CSSValueMarginBox>(range))
2751 list->append(boxValue.releaseNonNull());
2752 }
2753 }
2754 if (!list->length())
2755 return nullptr;
2756 return list;
2757}

2804static CSSValueID getBaselineKeyword(RefPtr<CSSValue> value)
2805{
2806 auto& primitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*value);
2807 if (primitiveValue.pairValue()) {
2808 ASSERT(primitiveValue.pairValue()->first()->valueID() == CSSValueLast);
2809 ASSERT(primitiveValue.pairValue()->second()->valueID() == CSSValueBaseline);
2810 return CSSValueLastBaseline;
2811 }
2812 ASSERT(primitiveValue.valueID() == CSSValueBaseline);
2813 return CSSValueBaseline;
2814}
2815
2816static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeBaselineKeyword(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
2817{
2818 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> preference = consumeIdent<CSSValueFirst, CSSValueLast>(range);
2819 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> baseline = consumeIdent<CSSValueBaseline>(range);
2820 if (!baseline)
2821 return nullptr;
2822 if (preference && preference->valueID() == CSSValueLast)
2823 return createPrimitiveValuePair(preference.releaseNonNull(), baseline.releaseNonNull(), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce);
2824 return baseline;
2825}
2826
2827using IsPositionKeyword = bool (*)(CSSValueID);
2828
2829static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeContentDistributionOverflowPosition(CSSParserTokenRange& range, IsPositionKeyword isPositionKeyword)
2830{
2831 ASSERT(isPositionKeyword);
2832 CSSValueID id = range.peek().id();
2833 if (identMatches<CSSValueNormal>(id))
2834 return CSSContentDistributionValue::create(CSSValueInvalid, range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id(), CSSValueInvalid);
2835
2836 if (isBaselineKeyword(id)) {
2837 RefPtr<CSSValue> baseline = consumeBaselineKeyword(range);
2838 if (!baseline)
2839 return nullptr;
2840 return CSSContentDistributionValue::create(CSSValueInvalid, getBaselineKeyword(baseline), CSSValueInvalid);
2841 }
2842
2843 if (isContentDistributionKeyword(id))
2844 return CSSContentDistributionValue::create(range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id(), CSSValueInvalid, CSSValueInvalid);
2845
2846 CSSValueID overflow = isOverflowKeyword(id) ? range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id() : CSSValueInvalid;
2847 if (isPositionKeyword(range.peek().id()))
2848 return CSSContentDistributionValue::create(CSSValueInvalid, range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id(), overflow);
2849
2850 return nullptr;
2851}

2868
2869static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeBorderImageSlice(CSSPropertyID property, CSSParserTokenRange& range)
2870{
2871 bool fill = consumeIdent<CSSValueFill>(range);
2872 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> slices[4] = { 0 };
2873
2874 for (size_t index = 0; index < 4; ++index) {
2875 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> value = consumePercent(range, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2876 if (!value)
2877 value = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2878 if (!value)
2879 break;
2880 slices[index] = value;
2881 }
2882 if (!slices[0])
2883 return nullptr;
2884 if (consumeIdent<CSSValueFill>(range)) {
2885 if (fill)
2886 return nullptr;
2887 fill = true;
2888 }
2889 complete4Sides(slices);
2890 // FIXME: For backwards compatibility, -webkit-border-image, -webkit-mask-box-image and -webkit-box-reflect have to do a fill by default.
2891 // FIXME: What do we do with -webkit-box-reflect and -webkit-mask-box-image? Probably just have to leave them filling...
2892 if (property == CSSPropertyWebkitBorderImage || property == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImage || property == CSSPropertyWebkitBoxReflect)
2893 fill = true;
2894
2895 // Now build a rect value to hold all four of our primitive values.
2896 // FIXME-NEWPARSER: Should just have a CSSQuadValue.
2897 auto quad = Quad::create();
2898 quad->setTop(slices[0].releaseNonNull());
2899 quad->setRight(slices[1].releaseNonNull());
2900 quad->setBottom(slices[2].releaseNonNull());
2901 quad->setLeft(slices[3].releaseNonNull());
2902
2903 // Make our new border image value now.
2904 return CSSBorderImageSliceValue::create(CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(WTFMove(quad)), fill);
2905}
2906
2907static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeBorderImageOutset(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
2908{
2909 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> outsets[4] = { 0 };
2910
2911 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> value;
2912 for (size_t index = 0; index < 4; ++index) {
2913 value = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2914 if (!value)
2915 value = consumeLength(range, HTMLStandardMode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2916 if (!value)
2917 break;
2918 outsets[index] = value;
2919 }
2920 if (!outsets[0])
2921 return nullptr;
2922 complete4Sides(outsets);
2923
2924 // FIXME-NEWPARSER: Should just have a CSSQuadValue.
2925 auto quad = Quad::create();
2926 quad->setTop(outsets[0].releaseNonNull());
2927 quad->setRight(outsets[1].releaseNonNull());
2928 quad->setBottom(outsets[2].releaseNonNull());
2929 quad->setLeft(outsets[3].releaseNonNull());
2930
2931 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(WTFMove(quad));
2932}
2933
2934static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeBorderImageWidth(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
2935{
2936 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> widths[4];
2937
2938 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> value;
2939 for (size_t index = 0; index < 4; ++index) {
2940 value = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2941 if (!value)
2942 value = consumeLengthOrPercent(range, HTMLStandardMode, ValueRange::NonNegative, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid);
2943 if (!value)
2944 value = consumeIdent<CSSValueAuto>(range);
2945 if (!value)
2946 break;
2947 widths[index] = value;
2948 }
2949 if (!widths[0])
2950 return nullptr;
2951 complete4Sides(widths);
2952
2953 // FIXME-NEWPARSER: Should just have a CSSQuadValue.
2954 auto quad = Quad::create();
2955 quad->setTop(widths[0].releaseNonNull());
2956 quad->setRight(widths[1].releaseNonNull());
2957 quad->setBottom(widths[2].releaseNonNull());
2958 quad->setLeft(widths[3].releaseNonNull());
2959
2960 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(WTFMove(quad));
2961}
