2963static bool consumeBorderImageComponents(CSSPropertyID property, CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, RefPtr<CSSValue>& source,
2964 RefPtr<CSSValue>& slice, RefPtr<CSSValue>& width, RefPtr<CSSValue>& outset, RefPtr<CSSValue>& repeat)
2965{
2966 do {
2967 if (!source) {
2968 source = consumeImageOrNone(range, context);
2969 if (source)
2970 continue;
2971 }
2972 if (!repeat) {
2973 repeat = consumeBorderImageRepeat(range);
2974 if (repeat)
2975 continue;
2976 }
2977 if (!slice) {
2978 slice = consumeBorderImageSlice(property, range);
2979 if (slice) {
2980 ASSERT(!width && !outset);
2981 if (consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(range)) {
2982 width = consumeBorderImageWidth(range);
2983 if (consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(range)) {
2984 outset = consumeBorderImageOutset(range);
2985 if (!outset)
2986 return false;
2987 } else if (!width) {
2988 return false;
2989 }
2990 }
2991 } else {
2992 return false;
2993 }
2994 } else {
2995 return false;
2996 }
2997 } while (!range.atEnd());
2998 return true;
2999}

3013static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeReflect(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
3014{
3015 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
3016 return consumeIdent(range);

3075static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumePrefixedBackgroundBox(CSSPropertyID property, CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& /*context*/)
3076{
3077 // The values 'border', 'padding' and 'content' are deprecated and do not apply to the version of the property that has the -webkit- prefix removed.
3078 if (RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> value = consumeIdentRange(range, CSSValueBorder, CSSValuePaddingBox))
3079 return value;
3080 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueWebkitText || ((property == CSSPropertyWebkitBackgroundClip || property == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskClip) && range.peek().id() == CSSValueText))

3085static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeBackgroundSize(CSSPropertyID property, CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
3086{
3087 if (identMatches<CSSValueContain, CSSValueCover>(range.peek().id()))
3088 return consumeIdent(range);
3089
3090 // FIXME: We're allowing the unitless quirk on this property because our
3091 // tests assume that. Other browser engines don't allow it though.
3092 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> horizontal = consumeIdent<CSSValueAuto>(range);
3093 if (!horizontal)
3094 horizontal = consumeLengthOrPercent(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::NonNegative, UnitlessQuirk::Allow);
3095
3096 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> vertical;
3097 if (!range.atEnd()) {
3098 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueAuto) // `auto' is the default
3099 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
3100 else
3101 vertical = consumeLengthOrPercent(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::NonNegative, UnitlessQuirk::Allow);
3102 } else if (!vertical && property == CSSPropertyWebkitBackgroundSize) {
3103 // Legacy syntax: "-webkit-background-size: 10px" is equivalent to "background-size: 10px 10px".
3104 vertical = horizontal;
3105 }
3106 if (!vertical)
3107 return horizontal;
3108 return createPrimitiveValuePair(horizontal.releaseNonNull(), vertical.releaseNonNull(), property == CSSPropertyWebkitBackgroundSize ? Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce : Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::DoNotCoalesce);
3109}

3111static RefPtr<CSSValueList> consumeGridAutoFlow(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3112{

3116 rowOrColumnValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueRow, CSSValueColumn>(range);

3128static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeBackgroundComponent(CSSPropertyID property, CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
3129{
3130 switch (property) {
3131 case CSSPropertyBackgroundClip:
3132 return consumeBackgroundClip(range);
3133 case CSSPropertyBackgroundBlendMode:
3134 return consumeBackgroundBlendMode(range);
3135 case CSSPropertyBackgroundAttachment:
3136 return consumeBackgroundAttachment(range);
3137 case CSSPropertyBackgroundOrigin:
3138 return consumeBackgroundBox(range);
3139 case CSSPropertyWebkitMaskComposite:
3140 case CSSPropertyWebkitBackgroundComposite:
3141 return consumeBackgroundComposite(range);
3142 case CSSPropertyWebkitBackgroundClip:
3143 case CSSPropertyWebkitBackgroundOrigin:
3144 case CSSPropertyWebkitMaskClip:
3145 case CSSPropertyWebkitMaskOrigin:

3160 case CSSPropertyWebkitMaskSize:
3161 return consumeBackgroundSize(property, range, context.mode);
3162 case CSSPropertyBackgroundColor:

3166 };

3171{

3177 }
3178 downcast<CSSValueList>(*list).append(WTFMove(value));
3179 } else {
3180 // To conserve memory we don't actually wrap a single value in a list.
3181 list = WTFMove(value);

3273static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeGridLine(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3274{
3275 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueAuto)
3276 return consumeIdent(range);
3277
3278 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> spanValue;
3279 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> gridLineName;

3285 spanValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueSpan>(range);
3286 if (spanValue) {
3287 numericValue = consumeInteger(range);
3288 gridLineName = consumeCustomIdentForGridLine(range);
3289 if (!numericValue)
3290 numericValue = consumeInteger(range);
3291 } else {
3292 gridLineName = consumeCustomIdentForGridLine(range);
3293 if (gridLineName) {
3294 numericValue = consumeInteger(range);
3295 spanValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueSpan>(range);
3296 if (!spanValue && !numericValue)
3297 return gridLineName;
3298 } else {
3299 return nullptr;
3300 }
3301 }
3302 }
3303
3304 if (spanValue && !numericValue && !gridLineName)
3305 return nullptr; // "span" keyword alone is invalid.
3306 if (spanValue && numericValue && numericValue->intValue() < 0)
3307 return nullptr; // Negative numbers are not allowed for span.
3308 if (numericValue && numericValue->intValue() == 0)
3309 return nullptr; // An <integer> value of zero makes the declaration invalid.
3310
3311 RefPtr<CSSValueList> values = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
3312 if (spanValue)
3313 values->append(spanValue.releaseNonNull());
3314 if (numericValue)
3315 values->append(numericValue.releaseNonNull());
3316 if (gridLineName)
3317 values->append(gridLineName.releaseNonNull());
3318 ASSERT(values->length());
3319 return values;
3320}
3321
3322static bool isGridTrackFixedSized(const CSSPrimitiveValue& primitiveValue)
3323{
3324 CSSValueID valueID = primitiveValue.valueID();
3325 if (valueID == CSSValueMinContent || valueID == CSSValueWebkitMinContent || valueID == CSSValueMaxContent || valueID == CSSValueWebkitMaxContent || valueID == CSSValueAuto || primitiveValue.isFlex())
3326 return false;
3327
3328 return true;
3329}
3330
3331static bool isGridTrackFixedSized(const CSSValue& value)
3332{
3333 if (value.isPrimitiveValue())
3334 return isGridTrackFixedSized(downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value));
3335
3336 ASSERT(value.isFunctionValue());
3337 auto& function = downcast<CSSFunctionValue>(value);
3338 if (function.name() == CSSValueFitContent || function.length() < 2)
3339 return false;
3340
3341 const CSSValue* minPrimitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(function.item(0));
3342 const CSSValue* maxPrimitiveValue = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(function.item(1));
3343 return isGridTrackFixedSized(*minPrimitiveValue) || isGridTrackFixedSized(*maxPrimitiveValue);
3344}
3345
3346static Vector<String> parseGridTemplateAreasColumnNames(StringView gridRowNames)
3347{
3348 ASSERT(!gridRowNames.isEmpty());
3349 Vector<String> columnNames;
3350 StringBuilder areaName;
3351 for (auto character : gridRowNames.codeUnits()) {
3352 if (isCSSSpace(character)) {
3353 if (!areaName.isEmpty()) {
3354 columnNames.append(areaName.toString());
3355 areaName.clear();
3356 }
3357 continue;
3358 }
3359 if (character == '.') {
3360 if (areaName == ".")
3361 continue;
3362 if (!areaName.isEmpty()) {
3363 columnNames.append(areaName.toString());
3364 areaName.clear();
3365 }
3366 } else {
3367 if (!isNameCodePoint(character))
3368 return Vector<String>();
3369 if (areaName == ".") {
3370 columnNames.append(areaName.toString());
3371 areaName.clear();
3372 }
3373 }
3374
3375 areaName.append(character);
3376 }
3377
3378 if (!areaName.isEmpty())
3379 columnNames.append(areaName.toString());
3380
3381 return columnNames;
3382}
3383
3384static bool parseGridTemplateAreasRow(StringView gridRowNames, NamedGridAreaMap& gridAreaMap, const size_t rowCount, size_t& columnCount)
3385{
3386 if (gridRowNames.isAllSpecialCharacters<isCSSSpace>())
3387 return false;
3388
3389 Vector<String> columnNames = parseGridTemplateAreasColumnNames(gridRowNames);
3390 if (rowCount == 0) {
3391 columnCount = columnNames.size();
3392 if (columnCount == 0)
3393 return false;
3394 } else if (columnCount != columnNames.size()) {
3395 // The declaration is invalid if all the rows don't have the number of columns.
3396 return false;
3397 }
3398
3399 for (size_t currentColumn = 0; currentColumn < columnCount; ++currentColumn) {
3400 const String& gridAreaName = columnNames[currentColumn];
3401
3402 // Unamed areas are always valid (we consider them to be 1x1).
3403 if (gridAreaName == ".")
3404 continue;
3405
3406 size_t lookAheadColumn = currentColumn + 1;
3407 while (lookAheadColumn < columnCount && columnNames[lookAheadColumn] == gridAreaName)
3408 lookAheadColumn++;
3409
3410 NamedGridAreaMap::iterator gridAreaIt = gridAreaMap.find(gridAreaName);
3411 if (gridAreaIt == gridAreaMap.end()) {
3412 gridAreaMap.add(gridAreaName, GridArea(GridSpan::translatedDefiniteGridSpan(rowCount, rowCount + 1), GridSpan::translatedDefiniteGridSpan(currentColumn, lookAheadColumn)));
3413 } else {
3414 GridArea& gridArea = gridAreaIt->value;
3415
3416 // The following checks test that the grid area is a single filled-in rectangle.
3417 // 1. The new row is adjacent to the previously parsed row.
3418 if (rowCount != gridArea.rows.endLine())
3419 return false;
3420
3421 // 2. The new area starts at the same position as the previously parsed area.
3422 if (currentColumn != gridArea.columns.startLine())
3423 return false;
3424
3425 // 3. The new area ends at the same position as the previously parsed area.
3426 if (lookAheadColumn != gridArea.columns.endLine())
3427 return false;
3428
3429 gridArea.rows = GridSpan::translatedDefiniteGridSpan(gridArea.rows.startLine(), gridArea.rows.endLine() + 1);
3430 }
3431 currentColumn = lookAheadColumn - 1;
3432 }
3433
3434 return true;
3435}
3436
3437static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeGridBreadth(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
3438{
3439 const CSSParserToken& token = range.peek();
3440 if (identMatches<CSSValueMinContent, CSSValueWebkitMinContent, CSSValueMaxContent, CSSValueWebkitMaxContent, CSSValueAuto>(token.id()))
3441 return consumeIdent(range);
3442 if (token.type() == DimensionToken && token.unitType() == CSSUnitType::CSS_FR) {
3443 if (range.peek().numericValue() < 0)
3444 return nullptr;
3445 return CSSPrimitiveValue::create(range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().numericValue(), CSSUnitType::CSS_FR);
3446 }
3447 return consumeLengthOrPercent(range, cssParserMode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3448}
3449
3450static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeGridTrackSize(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode)
3451{
3452 const CSSParserToken& token = range.peek();
3453 if (identMatches<CSSValueAuto>(token.id()))
3454 return consumeIdent(range);
3455
3456 if (token.functionId() == CSSValueMinmax) {
3457 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = range;
3458 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(rangeCopy);
3459 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> minTrackBreadth = consumeGridBreadth(args, cssParserMode);
3460 if (!minTrackBreadth || minTrackBreadth->isFlex() || !consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
3461 return nullptr;
3462 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> maxTrackBreadth = consumeGridBreadth(args, cssParserMode);
3463 if (!maxTrackBreadth || !args.atEnd())
3464 return nullptr;
3465 range = rangeCopy;
3466 RefPtr<CSSFunctionValue> result = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueMinmax);
3467 result->append(minTrackBreadth.releaseNonNull());
3468 result->append(maxTrackBreadth.releaseNonNull());
3469 return result;
3470 }
3471
3472 if (token.functionId() == CSSValueFitContent)
3473 return consumeFitContent(range, cssParserMode);
3474
3475 return consumeGridBreadth(range, cssParserMode);
3476}
3477
3478// Appends to the passed in CSSGridLineNamesValue if any, otherwise creates a new one. Returns nullptr if an empty list is consumed.
3479static RefPtr<CSSGridLineNamesValue> consumeGridLineNames(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSGridLineNamesValue* lineNames = nullptr)
3480{
3481 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = range;
3482 if (rangeCopy.consumeIncludingWhitespace().type() != LeftBracketToken)
3483 return nullptr;
3484
3485 RefPtr<CSSGridLineNamesValue> result = lineNames;
3486 if (!result)
3487 result = CSSGridLineNamesValue::create();
3488 while (RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> lineName = consumeCustomIdentForGridLine(rangeCopy))
3489 result->append(lineName.releaseNonNull());
3490 if (rangeCopy.consumeIncludingWhitespace().type() != RightBracketToken)
3491 return nullptr;
3492 range = rangeCopy;
3493 return result->length() ? result : nullptr;
3494}
3495
3496static bool consumeGridTrackRepeatFunction(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode, CSSValueList& list, bool& isAutoRepeat, bool& allTracksAreFixedSized)
3497{
3498 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(range);
3499 // The number of repetitions for <auto-repeat> is not important at parsing level
3500 // because it will be computed later, let's set it to 1.
3501 size_t repetitions = 1;
3502 isAutoRepeat = identMatches<CSSValueAutoFill, CSSValueAutoFit>(args.peek().id());
3503 RefPtr<CSSValueList> repeatedValues;
3504 if (isAutoRepeat)
3505 repeatedValues = CSSGridAutoRepeatValue::create(args.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id());
3506 else {
3507 auto repetition = consumePositiveIntegerRaw(args);
3508 if (!repetition)
3509 return false;
3510 repetitions = clampTo<size_t>(static_cast<size_t>(*repetition), 0, GridPosition::max());
3511 repeatedValues = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
3512 }
3513 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
3514 return false;
3515 RefPtr<CSSGridLineNamesValue> lineNames = consumeGridLineNames(args);
3516 if (lineNames)
3517 repeatedValues->append(lineNames.releaseNonNull());
3518
3519 size_t numberOfTracks = 0;
3520 while (!args.atEnd()) {
3521 RefPtr<CSSValue> trackSize = consumeGridTrackSize(args, cssParserMode);
3522 if (!trackSize)
3523 return false;
3524 if (allTracksAreFixedSized)
3525 allTracksAreFixedSized = isGridTrackFixedSized(*trackSize);
3526 repeatedValues->append(trackSize.releaseNonNull());
3527 ++numberOfTracks;
3528 lineNames = consumeGridLineNames(args);
3529 if (lineNames)
3530 repeatedValues->append(lineNames.releaseNonNull());
3531 }
3532 // We should have found at least one <track-size> or else it is not a valid <track-list>.
3533 if (!numberOfTracks)
3534 return false;
3535
3536 if (isAutoRepeat)
3537 list.append(repeatedValues.releaseNonNull());
3538 else {
3539 // We clamp the repetitions to a multiple of the repeat() track list's size, while staying below the max grid size.
3540 repetitions = std::min(repetitions, GridPosition::max() / numberOfTracks);
3541 RefPtr<CSSValueList> integerRepeatedValues = CSSGridIntegerRepeatValue::create(repetitions);
3542 for (size_t i = 0; i < repeatedValues->length(); ++i)
3543 integerRepeatedValues->append(*repeatedValues->itemWithoutBoundsCheck(i));
3544 list.append(integerRepeatedValues.releaseNonNull());
3545 }
3546 return true;
3547}
3548
3549enum TrackListType { GridTemplate, GridTemplateNoRepeat, GridAuto };
3550
3551static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeGridTrackList(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode cssParserMode, TrackListType trackListType)
3552{
3553 bool allowGridLineNames = trackListType != GridAuto;
3554 RefPtr<CSSValueList> values = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
3555 if (!allowGridLineNames && range.peek().type() == LeftBracketToken)
3556 return nullptr;
3557 RefPtr<CSSGridLineNamesValue> lineNames = consumeGridLineNames(range);
3558 if (lineNames)
3559 values->append(lineNames.releaseNonNull());
3560
3561 bool allowRepeat = trackListType == GridTemplate;
3562 bool seenAutoRepeat = false;
3563 bool allTracksAreFixedSized = true;
3564 do {
3565 bool isAutoRepeat;
3566 if (range.peek().functionId() == CSSValueRepeat) {
3567 if (!allowRepeat)
3568 return nullptr;
3569 if (!consumeGridTrackRepeatFunction(range, cssParserMode, *values, isAutoRepeat, allTracksAreFixedSized))
3570 return nullptr;
3571 if (isAutoRepeat && seenAutoRepeat)
3572 return nullptr;
3573 seenAutoRepeat = seenAutoRepeat || isAutoRepeat;
3574 } else if (RefPtr<CSSValue> value = consumeGridTrackSize(range, cssParserMode)) {
3575 if (allTracksAreFixedSized)
3576 allTracksAreFixedSized = isGridTrackFixedSized(*value);
3577 values->append(value.releaseNonNull());
3578 } else {
3579 return nullptr;
3580 }
3581 if (seenAutoRepeat && !allTracksAreFixedSized)
3582 return nullptr;
3583 if (!allowGridLineNames && range.peek().type() == LeftBracketToken)
3584 return nullptr;
3585 lineNames = consumeGridLineNames(range);
3586 if (lineNames)
3587 values->append(lineNames.releaseNonNull());
3588 } while (!range.atEnd() && range.peek().type() != DelimiterToken);
3589 return values;
3590}

3599static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeGridTemplateAreas(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3600{
3601 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
3602 return consumeIdent(range);
3603
3604 NamedGridAreaMap gridAreaMap;
3605 size_t rowCount = 0;
3606 size_t columnCount = 0;
3607
3608 while (range.peek().type() == StringToken) {
3609 if (!parseGridTemplateAreasRow(range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().value(), gridAreaMap, rowCount, columnCount))
3610 return nullptr;
3611 ++rowCount;
3612 }
3613
3614 if (rowCount == 0)
3615 return nullptr;
3616 ASSERT(columnCount);
3617 return CSSGridTemplateAreasValue::create(gridAreaMap, rowCount, columnCount);
3618}

3620static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeLineBoxContain(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3621{
3622 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
3623 return consumeIdent(range);
3624
3625 OptionSet<LineBoxContain> lineBoxContain;
3626
3627 while (range.peek().type() == IdentToken) {
3628 auto id = range.peek().id();
3629 if (id == CSSValueBlock) {
3630 if (lineBoxContain.contains(LineBoxContain::Block))
3631 return nullptr;
3632 lineBoxContain.add(LineBoxContain::Block);
3633 } else if (id == CSSValueInline) {
3634 if (lineBoxContain.contains(LineBoxContain::Inline))
3635 return nullptr;
3636 lineBoxContain.add(LineBoxContain::Inline);
3637 } else if (id == CSSValueFont) {
3638 if (lineBoxContain.contains(LineBoxContain::Font))
3639 return nullptr;
3640 lineBoxContain.add(LineBoxContain::Font);
3641 } else if (id == CSSValueGlyphs) {
3642 if (lineBoxContain.contains(LineBoxContain::Glyphs))
3643 return nullptr;
3644 lineBoxContain.add(LineBoxContain::Glyphs);
3645 } else if (id == CSSValueReplaced) {
3646 if (lineBoxContain.contains(LineBoxContain::Replaced))
3647 return nullptr;
3648 lineBoxContain.add(LineBoxContain::Replaced);
3649 } else if (id == CSSValueInlineBox) {
3650 if (lineBoxContain.contains(LineBoxContain::InlineBox))
3651 return nullptr;
3652 lineBoxContain.add(LineBoxContain::InlineBox);
3653 } else if (id == CSSValueInitialLetter) {
3654 if (lineBoxContain.contains(LineBoxContain::InitialLetter))
3655 return nullptr;
3656 lineBoxContain.add(LineBoxContain::InitialLetter);
3657 } else
3658 return nullptr;
3659 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
3660 }
3661
3662 if (!lineBoxContain)
3663 return nullptr;
3664
3665 return CSSLineBoxContainValue::create(lineBoxContain);
3666}

3675static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeInitialLetter(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3676{
3677 RefPtr<CSSValue> ident = consumeIdent<CSSValueNormal>(range);
3678 if (ident)
3679 return ident;
3680
3681 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> height = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3682 if (!height)
3683 return nullptr;
3684
3685 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> position;
3686 if (!range.atEnd()) {
3687 position = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3688 if (!position || !range.atEnd())
3689 return nullptr;

3695
3696static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeSpeakAs(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3697{
3698 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
3699 return consumeIdent(range);
3700
3701 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
3702
3703 bool seenNormal = false;
3704 bool seenSpellOut = false;
3705 bool seenLiteralPunctuation = false;
3706 bool seenNoPunctuation = false;
3707
3708 // normal | spell-out || digits || [ literal-punctuation | no-punctuation ]
3709 while (!range.atEnd()) {
3710 CSSValueID valueID = range.peek().id();
3711 if ((valueID == CSSValueNormal && seenSpellOut)
3712 || (valueID == CSSValueSpellOut && seenNormal)
3713 || (valueID == CSSValueLiteralPunctuation && seenNoPunctuation)
3714 || (valueID == CSSValueNoPunctuation && seenLiteralPunctuation))
3715 return nullptr;
3716 RefPtr<CSSValue> ident = consumeIdent<CSSValueNormal, CSSValueSpellOut, CSSValueDigits, CSSValueLiteralPunctuation, CSSValueNoPunctuation>(range);
3717 if (!ident)
3718 return nullptr;
3719 switch (valueID) {
3720 case CSSValueNormal:
3721 seenNormal = true;
3722 break;
3723 case CSSValueSpellOut:
3724 seenSpellOut = true;
3725 break;
3726 case CSSValueLiteralPunctuation:
3727 seenLiteralPunctuation = true;
3728 break;
3729 case CSSValueNoPunctuation:
3730 seenNoPunctuation = true;
3731 break;
3732 default:
3733 break;
3734 }
3735 list->append(ident.releaseNonNull());
3736 }
3737
3738 return list->length() ? list : nullptr;
3739}

3741static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeHangingPunctuation(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3742{
3743 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
3744 return consumeIdent(range);
3745
3746 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
3747
3748 bool seenForceEnd = false;
3749 bool seenAllowEnd = false;
3750 bool seenFirst = false;
3751 bool seenLast = false;
3752
3753 while (!range.atEnd()) {
3754 CSSValueID valueID = range.peek().id();
3755 if ((valueID == CSSValueFirst && seenFirst)
3756 || (valueID == CSSValueLast && seenLast)
3757 || (valueID == CSSValueAllowEnd && (seenAllowEnd || seenForceEnd))
3758 || (valueID == CSSValueForceEnd && (seenAllowEnd || seenForceEnd)))
3759 return nullptr;
3760 RefPtr<CSSValue> ident = consumeIdent<CSSValueAllowEnd, CSSValueForceEnd, CSSValueFirst, CSSValueLast>(range);
3761 if (!ident)
3762 return nullptr;
3763 switch (valueID) {
3764 case CSSValueAllowEnd:
3765 seenAllowEnd = true;
3766 break;
3767 case CSSValueForceEnd:
3768 seenForceEnd = true;
3769 break;
3770 case CSSValueFirst:
3771 seenFirst = true;
3772 break;
3773 case CSSValueLast:
3774 seenLast = true;
3775 break;
3776 default:
3777 break;
3778 }
3779 list->append(ident.releaseNonNull());
3780 }
3781
3782 return list->length() ? list : nullptr;
3783}

3811static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeAspectRatio(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3812{
3813 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> autoValue;
3814 if (range.peek().type() == IdentToken)
3815 autoValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueAuto>(range);
3816
3817 if (range.atEnd())
3818 return RefPtr<CSSValue>(WTFMove(autoValue));
3819
3820 auto leftValue = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3821 if (!leftValue)
3822 return nullptr;
3823
3824 bool slashSeen = consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(range);
3825
3826 auto rightValue = consumeNumber(range, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3827 if ((rightValue && !slashSeen) || (!rightValue && slashSeen))
3828 return nullptr;
3829 if (!slashSeen && !rightValue) // A missing right-hand is treated as 1.
3830 rightValue = CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(1, CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
3831 if (!autoValue)
3832 autoValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueAuto>(range);
3833
3834 auto ratioList = CSSValueList::createSlashSeparated();
3835 ratioList->append(leftValue.releaseNonNull());
3836 if (rightValue)
3837 ratioList->append(rightValue.releaseNonNull());
3838 if (!autoValue)
3839 return RefPtr<CSSValue>(WTFMove(ratioList));
3840 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
3841 list->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto));
3842 list->append(ratioList);
3843 return RefPtr<CSSValue>(WTFMove(list));
3844}

3846static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeContain(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3847{
3848 if (auto singleValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueNone, CSSValueStrict, CSSValueContent>(range))
3849 return singleValue;
3850 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
3851 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> size, layout, paint;
3852 while (!range.atEnd()) {
3853 switch (range.peek().id()) {
3854 case CSSValueSize:
3855 if (size)
3856 return nullptr;
3857 size = consumeIdent(range);
3858 break;
3859 case CSSValueLayout:
3860 if (layout)
3861 return nullptr;
3862 layout = consumeIdent(range);
3863 break;
3864 case CSSValuePaint:
3865 if (paint)
3866 return nullptr;
3867 paint = consumeIdent(range);
3868 break;
3869 default:
3870 return nullptr;
3871 }
3872 }
3873 if (size)
3874 list->append(size.releaseNonNull());
3875 if (layout)
3876 list->append(layout.releaseNonNull());
3877 if (paint)
3878 list->append(paint.releaseNonNull());
3879 if (!list->length())
3880 return nullptr;
3881 return RefPtr<CSSValue>(WTFMove(list));
3882}

3884static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeTextEmphasisPosition(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3885{
3886 bool foundOverOrUnder = false;
3887 CSSValueID overUnderValueID = CSSValueOver;
3888 bool foundLeftOrRight = false;
3889 CSSValueID leftRightValueID = CSSValueRight;
3890 while (!range.atEnd()) {
3891 switch (range.peek().id()) {
3892 case CSSValueOver:
3893 if (foundOverOrUnder)
3894 return nullptr;
3895 foundOverOrUnder = true;
3896 overUnderValueID = CSSValueOver;
3897 break;
3898 case CSSValueUnder:
3899 if (foundOverOrUnder)
3900 return nullptr;
3901 foundOverOrUnder = true;
3902 overUnderValueID = CSSValueUnder;
3903 break;
3904 case CSSValueLeft:
3905 if (foundLeftOrRight)
3906 return nullptr;
3907 foundLeftOrRight = true;
3908 leftRightValueID = CSSValueLeft;
3909 break;
3910 case CSSValueRight:
3911 if (foundLeftOrRight)
3912 return nullptr;
3913 foundLeftOrRight = true;
3914 leftRightValueID = CSSValueRight;
3915 break;
3916 default:
3917 return nullptr;
3918 }
3919
3920 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
3921 }
3922 if (!foundOverOrUnder)
3923 return nullptr;
3924 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
3925 list->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(overUnderValueID));
3926 if (foundLeftOrRight)
3927 list->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(leftRightValueID));
3928 return list;
3929}

3931#if ENABLE(DARK_MODE_CSS)
3932
3933static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeColorScheme(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3934{
3935 if (isAuto(range.peek().id()))
3936 return consumeIdent(range);
3937
3938 Vector<CSSValueID, 3> identifiers;
3939
3940 while (!range.atEnd()) {
3941 if (range.peek().type() != IdentToken)
3942 return nullptr;
3943
3944 CSSValueID id = range.peek().id();
3945
3946 switch (id) {
3947 case CSSValueAuto:
3948 // Auto is only allowed as a single value, and was handled earlier.
3949 // Don't allow it in the list.
3950 return nullptr;
3951
3952 case CSSValueOnly:
3953 case CSSValueLight:
3954 case CSSValueDark:
3955 if (!identifiers.appendIfNotContains(id))
3956 return nullptr;
3957 break;
3958
3959 default:
3960 // Unknown identifiers are allowed and ignored.
3961 break;
3962 }
3963
3964 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
3965 }
3966
3967 RefPtr<CSSValueList> list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
3968 for (auto id : identifiers)
3969 list->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(id));
3970 return list;
3971}
3972
3973#endif
