4476
4477bool CSSPropertyParser::canParseTypedCustomPropertyValue(const String& syntax)
4478{
4479 if (syntax != "*") {
4480 m_range.consumeWhitespace();
4481
4482 // First check for keywords
4483 CSSValueID id = m_range.peek().id();
4484 if (id == CSSValueInherit || id == CSSValueInitial || id == CSSValueRevert)
4485 return true;
4486
4487 auto localRange = m_range;
4488 while (!localRange.atEnd()) {
4489 auto id = localRange.consume().functionId();
4490 if (id == CSSValueVar || id == CSSValueEnv)
4491 return true; // For variables, we just permit everything
4492 }
4493
4494 auto primitiveVal = consumeWidthOrHeight(m_range, m_context);
4495 if (primitiveVal && primitiveVal->isPrimitiveValue() && m_range.atEnd())
4496 return true;
4497 return false;
4498 }
4499
4500 return true;
4501}
4502
4503void CSSPropertyParser::collectParsedCustomPropertyValueDependencies(const String& syntax, bool isRoot, HashSet<CSSPropertyID>& dependencies)
4504{
4505 if (syntax != "*") {
4506 m_range.consumeWhitespace();
4507 auto primitiveVal = consumeWidthOrHeight(m_range, m_context);
4508 if (!m_range.atEnd())
4509 return;
4510 if (primitiveVal && primitiveVal->isPrimitiveValue()) {
4511 primitiveVal->collectDirectComputationalDependencies(dependencies);
4512 if (isRoot)
4513 primitiveVal->collectDirectRootComputationalDependencies(dependencies);
4514 }
4515 }
4516}
4517
4518RefPtr<CSSCustomPropertyValue> CSSPropertyParser::parseTypedCustomPropertyValue(const String& name, const String& syntax, const Style::BuilderState& builderState)
4519{
4520 if (syntax != "*") {
4521 m_range.consumeWhitespace();
4522 auto primitiveVal = consumeWidthOrHeight(m_range, m_context);
4523 if (primitiveVal && primitiveVal->isPrimitiveValue() && downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*primitiveVal).isLength()) {
4524 auto length = Style::BuilderConverter::convertLength(builderState, *primitiveVal);
4525 if (!length.isCalculated() && !length.isUndefined())
4526 return CSSCustomPropertyValue::createSyntaxLength(name, WTFMove(length));
4527 }
4528 } else {
4529 auto propertyValue = CSSCustomPropertyValue::createSyntaxAll(name, CSSVariableData::create(m_range));
4530 while (!m_range.atEnd())
4531 m_range.consume();
4532 return { WTFMove(propertyValue) };
4533 }
4534
4535 return nullptr;
4536}
4537
4538// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#counter-style-system
4539static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeCounterStyleSystem(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
4540{
4541 if (auto ident = consumeIdent<CSSValueCyclic, CSSValueNumeric, CSSValueAlphabetic, CSSValueSymbolic, CSSValueAdditive>(range))
4542 return ident;
4543
4544 if (auto ident = consumeIdent<CSSValueFixed>(range)) {
4545 if (range.atEnd())
4546 return ident;
4547 // If we have the `fixed` keyword but the range is not at the end, the next token must be a integer.
4548 // If it's not, this value is invalid.
4549 auto firstSymbolValue = consumeInteger(range);
4550 if (!firstSymbolValue)
4551 return nullptr;
4552 return createPrimitiveValuePair(ident.releaseNonNull(), firstSymbolValue.releaseNonNull());
4553 }
4554
4555 if (auto ident = consumeIdent<CSSValueExtends>(range)) {
4556 // There must be a `<counter-style-name>` following the `extends` keyword. If there isn't, this value is invalid.
4557 auto parsedCounterStyleName = consumeCounterStyleName(range);
4558 if (!parsedCounterStyleName)
4559 return nullptr;
4560 return createPrimitiveValuePair(ident.releaseNonNull(), parsedCounterStyleName.releaseNonNull());
4561 }
4562 return nullptr;
4563}
4564
4565// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#typedef-symbol
4566static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCounterStyleSymbol(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
4567{
4568 if (auto string = consumeString(range))
4569 return string;
4570 if (auto customIdent = consumeCustomIdent(range))
4571 return customIdent;
4572 // There are inherent difficulties in supporting <image> symbols in @counter-styles, so gate them behind a
4573 // flag for now. https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=167645
4574 if (context.counterStyleAtRuleImageSymbolsEnabled) {
4575 if (auto image = consumeImage(range, context, { AllowedImageType::URLFunction, AllowedImageType::GeneratedImage }))
4576 return image;
4577 }
4578 return nullptr;
4579}
4580
4581// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#counter-style-negative
4582static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCounterStyleNegative(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
4583{
4584 auto prependValue = consumeCounterStyleSymbol(range, context);
4585 if (!prependValue)
4586 return nullptr;
4587 if (range.atEnd())
4588 return prependValue;
4589
4590 auto appendValue = consumeCounterStyleSymbol(range, context);
4591 if (!appendValue || !range.atEnd())
4592 return nullptr;
4593
4594 RefPtr<CSSValueList> values = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
4595 values->append(prependValue.releaseNonNull());
4596 values->append(appendValue.releaseNonNull());
4597 return values;
4598}
4599
4600// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#counter-style-range
4601static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeCounterStyleRangeBound(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
4602{
4603 if (auto infinite = consumeIdent<CSSValueInfinite>(range))
4604 return infinite;
4605 if (auto integer = consumeInteger(range))
4606 return integer;
4607 return nullptr;
4608}
4609
4610// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#counter-style-range
4611static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCounterStyleRange(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
4612{
4613 if (auto autoValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueAuto>(range))
4614 return autoValue;
4615
4616 auto rangeList = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
4617 do {
4618 auto lowerBound = consumeCounterStyleRangeBound(range);
4619 if (!lowerBound)
4620 return nullptr;
4621 auto upperBound = consumeCounterStyleRangeBound(range);
4622 if (!upperBound)
4623 return nullptr;
4624
4625 // If the lower bound of any range is higher than the upper bound, the entire descriptor is invalid and must be
4626 // ignored.
4627 if (lowerBound->isNumber() && upperBound->isNumber() && lowerBound->intValue() > upperBound->intValue())
4628 return nullptr;
4629 rangeList->append(createPrimitiveValuePair(lowerBound.releaseNonNull(), upperBound.releaseNonNull(), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::DoNotCoalesce));
4630 } while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(range));
4631 if (!range.atEnd() || !rangeList->length())
4632 return nullptr;
4633 return rangeList;
4634}
4635
4636// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#counter-style-pad
4637static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCounterStylePad(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
4638{
4639 RefPtr<CSSValue> integer;
4640 RefPtr<CSSValue> symbol;
4641 while (!integer || !symbol) {
4642 if (!integer) {
4643 integer = consumeInteger(range, 0);
4644 if (integer)
4645 continue;
4646 }
4647 if (!symbol) {
4648 symbol = consumeCounterStyleSymbol(range, context);
4649 if (symbol)
4650 continue;
4651 }
4652 return nullptr;
4653 }
4654 if (!range.atEnd())
4655 return nullptr;
4656 auto values = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
4657 values->append(integer.releaseNonNull());
4658 values->append(symbol.releaseNonNull());
4659 return values;
4660}
4661
4662// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#counter-style-symbols
4663static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCounterStyleSymbols(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
4664{
4665 auto symbols = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
4666 while (!range.atEnd()) {
4667 auto symbol = consumeCounterStyleSymbol(range, context);
4668 if (!symbol)
4669 return nullptr;
4670 symbols->append(symbol.releaseNonNull());
4671 }
4672 if (!symbols->length())
4673 return nullptr;
4674 return symbols;
4675}
4676
4677// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#counter-style-symbols
4678static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCounterStyleAdditiveSymbols(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
4679{
4680 auto values = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
4681 std::optional<int> lastWeight;
4682 do {
4683 auto integer = consumeInteger(range, 0);
4684 auto symbol = consumeCounterStyleSymbol(range, context);
4685 if (!integer) {
4686 if (!symbol)
4687 return nullptr;
4688 integer = consumeInteger(range, 0);
4689 if (!integer)
4690 return nullptr;
4691 }
4692
4693 // Additive tuples must be specified in order of strictly descending weight.
4694 auto weight = integer->intValue();
4695 if (lastWeight && !(weight < lastWeight))
4696 return nullptr;
4697 lastWeight = weight;
4698
4699 auto pair = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
4700 pair->append(integer.releaseNonNull());
4701 pair->append(symbol.releaseNonNull());
4702 values->append(WTFMove(pair));
4703 } while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(range));
4704 if (!range.atEnd() || !values->length())
4705 return nullptr;
4706 return values;
4707}
4708
4709// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#counter-style-speak-as
4710static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeCounterStyleSpeakAs(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
4711{
4712 if (auto speakAsIdent = consumeIdent<CSSValueAuto, CSSValueBullets, CSSValueNumbers, CSSValueWords, CSSValueSpellOut>(range))
4713 return speakAsIdent;
4714 return consumeCounterStyleName(range);
4715}
4716
4717RefPtr<CSSValue> CSSPropertyParser::parseCounterStyleDescriptor(CSSPropertyID propId, CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
4718{
4719 if (!context.counterStyleAtRulesEnabled)
4720 return nullptr;
4721
4722 switch (propId) {
4723 case CSSPropertySystem:
4724 return consumeCounterStyleSystem(range);
4725 case CSSPropertyNegative:
4726 return consumeCounterStyleNegative(range, context);
4727 case CSSPropertyPrefix:
4728 case CSSPropertySuffix:
4729 return consumeCounterStyleSymbol(range, context);
4730 case CSSPropertyRange:
4731 return consumeCounterStyleRange(range);
4732 case CSSPropertyPad:
4733 return consumeCounterStylePad(range, context);
4734 case CSSPropertyFallback:
4735 return consumeCounterStyleName(range);
4736 case CSSPropertySymbols:
4737 return consumeCounterStyleSymbols(range, context);
4738 case CSSPropertyAdditiveSymbols:
4739 return consumeCounterStyleAdditiveSymbols(range, context);
4740 case CSSPropertySpeakAs:
4741 return consumeCounterStyleSpeakAs(range);
4742 default:
4743 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4744 return nullptr;
4745 }
4746}
4747
4748bool CSSPropertyParser::parseCounterStyleDescriptor(CSSPropertyID propId, const CSSParserContext& context)
4749{
4750 auto parsedValue = parseCounterStyleDescriptor(propId, m_range, context);
4751 if (!parsedValue || !m_range.atEnd())
4752 return false;
4753
4754 addProperty(propId, CSSPropertyInvalid, *parsedValue, false);
4755 return true;
4756}
4757
4758bool CSSPropertyParser::parseFontFaceDescriptor(CSSPropertyID propId)
4759{
4760 RefPtr<CSSValue> parsedValue;
4761 switch (propId) {
4762 case CSSPropertyFontFamily:
4763 parsedValue = consumeFontFamilyDescriptor(m_range);
4764 break;
4765 case CSSPropertySrc: // This is a list of urls or local references.
4766 parsedValue = consumeFontFaceSrc(m_range, m_context);
4767 break;
4768 case CSSPropertyUnicodeRange:
4769 parsedValue = consumeFontFaceUnicodeRange(m_range);
4770 break;
4771 case CSSPropertyFontDisplay:
4772 parsedValue = consumeFontFaceFontDisplay(m_range, CSSValuePool::singleton());
4773 break;
4774 case CSSPropertyFontWeight:
4775#if ENABLE(VARIATION_FONTS)
4776 parsedValue = consumeFontWeightAbsoluteRange(m_range, CSSValuePool::singleton());
4777#else
4778 parsedValue = consumeFontWeightAbsolute(m_range, CSSValuePool::singleton());
4779#endif
4780 break;
4781 case CSSPropertyFontStretch:
4782#if ENABLE(VARIATION_FONTS)
4783 parsedValue = consumeFontStretchRange(m_range, CSSValuePool::singleton());
4784#else
4785 parsedValue = consumeFontStretch(m_range, CSSValuePool::singleton());
4786#endif
4787 break;
4788 case CSSPropertyFontStyle:
4789#if ENABLE(VARIATION_FONTS)
4790 parsedValue = consumeFontStyleRange(m_range, m_context.mode, CSSValuePool::singleton());
4791#else
4792 parsedValue = consumeFontStyle(m_range, m_context.mode, CSSValuePool::singleton());
4793#endif
4794 break;
4795 case CSSPropertyFontVariantCaps:
4796 parsedValue = consumeFontVariantCaps(m_range);
4797 break;
4798 case CSSPropertyFontVariantLigatures:
4799 parsedValue = consumeFontVariantLigatures(m_range);
4800 break;
4801 case CSSPropertyFontVariantNumeric:
4802 parsedValue = consumeFontVariantNumeric(m_range);
4803 break;
4804 case CSSPropertyFontVariantEastAsian:
4805 parsedValue = consumeFontVariantEastAsian(m_range);
4806 break;
4807 case CSSPropertyFontVariantAlternates:
4808 parsedValue = consumeFontVariantAlternates(m_range);
4809 break;
4810 case CSSPropertyFontVariantPosition:
4811 parsedValue = consumeFontVariantPosition(m_range);
4812 break;
4813 case CSSPropertyFontVariant:
4814 return consumeFontVariantShorthand(false);
4815 case CSSPropertyFontFeatureSettings:
4816 parsedValue = consumeFontFeatureSettings(m_range, CSSValuePool::singleton());
4817 break;
4818 default:
4819 break;
4820 }
4821
4822 if (!parsedValue || !m_range.atEnd())
4823 return false;
4824
4825 addProperty(propId, CSSPropertyInvalid, *parsedValue, false);
4826 return true;
4827}
4828
4829bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeSystemFont(bool important)
4830{
4831 CSSValueID systemFontID = m_range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id();
4832 ASSERT(systemFontID >= CSSValueCaption && systemFontID <= CSSValueStatusBar);
4833 if (!m_range.atEnd())
4834 return false;
4835
4836 FontCascadeDescription fontDescription;
4837 RenderTheme::singleton().systemFont(systemFontID, fontDescription);
4838 if (!fontDescription.isAbsoluteSize())
4839 return false;
4840
4841 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontStyle, CSSPropertyFont, CSSFontStyleValue::create(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(isItalic(fontDescription.italic()) ? CSSValueItalic : CSSValueNormal)), important);
4842 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontWeight, CSSPropertyFont, CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(static_cast<float>(fontDescription.weight())), important);
4843 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontSize, CSSPropertyFont, CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(fontDescription.specifiedSize(), CSSUnitType::CSS_PX), important);
4844 Ref<CSSValueList> fontFamilyList = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
4845 fontFamilyList->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createFontFamilyValue(fontDescription.familyAt(0), FromSystemFontID::Yes));
4846 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontFamily, CSSPropertyFont, WTFMove(fontFamilyList), important);
4847 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantCaps, CSSPropertyFont, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important);
4848 addProperty(CSSPropertyLineHeight, CSSPropertyFont, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important);
4849
4850 // FIXME_NEWPARSER: What about FontVariantNumeric and FontVariantLigatures?
4851
4852 return true;
4853}
4854
4855bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeFont(bool important)
4856{
4857 // Let's check if there is an inherit or initial somewhere in the shorthand.
4858 CSSParserTokenRange range = m_range;
4859 while (!range.atEnd()) {
4860 CSSValueID id = range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id();
4861 if (id == CSSValueInherit || id == CSSValueInitial)
4862 return false;
4863 }
4864 // Optional font-style, font-variant, font-stretch and font-weight.
4865 RefPtr<CSSFontStyleValue> fontStyle;
4866 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> fontVariantCaps;
4867 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> fontWeight;
4868 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> fontStretch;
4869
4870 while (!m_range.atEnd()) {
4871 CSSValueID id = m_range.peek().id();
4872 if (!fontStyle) {
4873 fontStyle = consumeFontStyle(m_range, m_context.mode, CSSValuePool::singleton());
4874 if (fontStyle)
4875 continue;
4876 }
4877 if (!fontVariantCaps && (id == CSSValueNormal || id == CSSValueSmallCaps)) {
4878 // Font variant in the shorthand is particular, it only accepts normal or small-caps.
4879 // See https://drafts.csswg.org/css-fonts/#propdef-font
4880 fontVariantCaps = consumeFontVariantCSS21(m_range);
4881 if (fontVariantCaps)
4882 continue;
4883 }
4884 if (!fontWeight) {
4885 fontWeight = consumeFontWeight(m_range);
4886 if (fontWeight)
4887 continue;
4888 }
4889 if (!fontStretch) {
4890 fontStretch = consumeFontStretchKeywordValue(m_range, CSSValuePool::singleton());
4891 if (fontStretch)
4892 continue;
4893 }
4894 break;
4895 }
4896
4897 if (m_range.atEnd())
4898 return false;
4899
4900 bool hasStyle = fontStyle;
4901 bool hasVariant = fontVariantCaps;
4902 bool hasWeight = fontWeight;
4903 bool hasStretch = fontStretch;
4904
4905 if (!fontStyle)
4906 fontStyle = CSSFontStyleValue::create(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal));
4907
4908 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontStyle, CSSPropertyFont, fontStyle.releaseNonNull(), important, !hasStyle);
4909 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantCaps, CSSPropertyFont, fontVariantCaps ? fontVariantCaps.releaseNonNull() : CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, !hasVariant);
4910/*
4911 // FIXME-NEWPARSER: What do we do with these? They aren't part of our fontShorthand().
4912 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantLigatures, CSSPropertyFont, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, true);
4913 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantNumeric, CSSPropertyFont, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, true);
4914*/
4915
4916 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontWeight, CSSPropertyFont, fontWeight ? fontWeight.releaseNonNull() : CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, !hasWeight);
4917 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontStretch, CSSPropertyFont, fontStretch ? fontStretch.releaseNonNull() : CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, !hasStretch);
4918
4919 // Now a font size _must_ come.
4920 RefPtr<CSSValue> fontSize = consumeFontSize(m_range, m_context.mode);
4921 if (!fontSize || m_range.atEnd())
4922 return false;
4923
4924 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontSize, CSSPropertyFont, *fontSize, important);
4925
4926 if (consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range)) {
4927 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> lineHeight = consumeLineHeight(m_range, m_context.mode);
4928 if (!lineHeight)
4929 return false;
4930 addProperty(CSSPropertyLineHeight, CSSPropertyFont, lineHeight.releaseNonNull(), important);
4931 } else
4932 addProperty(CSSPropertyLineHeight, CSSPropertyFont, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, true);
4933
4934 // Font family must come now.
4935 RefPtr<CSSValue> parsedFamilyValue = consumeFontFamily(m_range);
4936 if (!parsedFamilyValue)
4937 return false;
4938
4939 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontFamily, CSSPropertyFont, parsedFamilyValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
4940
4941 return m_range.atEnd();
4942}
4943
4944bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeFontVariantShorthand(bool important)
4945{
4946 if (identMatches<CSSValueNormal, CSSValueNone>(m_range.peek().id())) {
4947 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantLigatures, CSSPropertyFontVariant, consumeIdent(m_range).releaseNonNull(), important);
4948 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantCaps, CSSPropertyFontVariant, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, true);
4949 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantEastAsian, CSSPropertyFontVariant, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, true);
4950 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantPosition, CSSPropertyFontVariant, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, true);
4951 return m_range.atEnd();
4952 }
4953
4954 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> capsValue;
4955 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> alternatesValue;
4956 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> positionValue;
4957
4958 RefPtr<CSSValue> eastAsianValue;
4959 FontVariantLigaturesParser ligaturesParser;
4960 FontVariantNumericParser numericParser;
4961 bool implicitLigatures = true;
4962 bool implicitNumeric = true;
4963 do {
4964 if (!capsValue) {
4965 capsValue = consumeFontVariantCaps(m_range);
4966 if (capsValue)
4967 continue;
4968 }
4969
4970 if (!positionValue) {
4971 positionValue = consumeFontVariantPosition(m_range);
4972 if (positionValue)
4973 continue;
4974 }
4975
4976 if (!alternatesValue) {
4977 alternatesValue = consumeFontVariantAlternates(m_range);
4978 if (alternatesValue)
4979 continue;
4980 }
4981
4982 FontVariantLigaturesParser::ParseResult ligaturesParseResult = ligaturesParser.consumeLigature(m_range);
4983 FontVariantNumericParser::ParseResult numericParseResult = numericParser.consumeNumeric(m_range);
4984 if (ligaturesParseResult == FontVariantLigaturesParser::ParseResult::ConsumedValue) {
4985 implicitLigatures = false;
4986 continue;
4987 }
4988 if (numericParseResult == FontVariantNumericParser::ParseResult::ConsumedValue) {
4989 implicitNumeric = false;
4990 continue;
4991 }
4992
4993 if (ligaturesParseResult == FontVariantLigaturesParser::ParseResult::DisallowedValue
4994 || numericParseResult == FontVariantNumericParser::ParseResult::DisallowedValue)
4995 return false;
4996
4997 if (!eastAsianValue) {
4998 eastAsianValue = consumeFontVariantEastAsian(m_range);
4999 if (eastAsianValue)
5000 continue;
5001 }
5002
5003 // Saw some value that didn't match anything else.
5004 return false;
5005
5006 } while (!m_range.atEnd());
5007
5008 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantLigatures, CSSPropertyFontVariant, ligaturesParser.finalizeValue().releaseNonNull(), important, implicitLigatures);
5009 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantNumeric, CSSPropertyFontVariant, numericParser.finalizeValue().releaseNonNull(), important, implicitNumeric);
5010 bool implicitCaps = !capsValue;
5011 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantCaps, CSSPropertyFontVariant, capsValue ? capsValue.releaseNonNull() : CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, implicitCaps);
5012 bool implicitAlternates = !alternatesValue;
5013 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantAlternates, CSSPropertyFontVariant, alternatesValue ? alternatesValue.releaseNonNull() : CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, implicitAlternates);
5014 bool implicitPosition = !positionValue;
5015 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantPosition, CSSPropertyFontVariant, positionValue ? positionValue.releaseNonNull() : CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal), important, implicitPosition);
5016
5017 bool implicitEastAsian = !eastAsianValue;
5018 if (!eastAsianValue)
5019 eastAsianValue = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal);
5020 addProperty(CSSPropertyFontVariantEastAsian, CSSPropertyFontVariant, eastAsianValue.releaseNonNull(), important, implicitEastAsian);
5021
5022 return true;
5023}
5024
5025bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeBorderSpacing(bool important)
5026{
5027 RefPtr<CSSValue> horizontalSpacing = consumeLength(m_range, m_context.mode, ValueRange::NonNegative, UnitlessQuirk::Allow);
5028 if (!horizontalSpacing)
5029 return false;
5030 RefPtr<CSSValue> verticalSpacing = horizontalSpacing;
5031 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5032 verticalSpacing = consumeLength(m_range, m_context.mode, ValueRange::NonNegative, UnitlessQuirk::Allow);
5033 if (!verticalSpacing || !m_range.atEnd())
5034 return false;
5035 addProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitBorderHorizontalSpacing, CSSPropertyBorderSpacing, horizontalSpacing.releaseNonNull(), important);
5036 addProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitBorderVerticalSpacing, CSSPropertyBorderSpacing, verticalSpacing.releaseNonNull(), important);
5037 return true;
5038}
5039
5040bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeColumns(bool important)
5041{
5042 RefPtr<CSSValue> columnWidth;
5043 RefPtr<CSSValue> columnCount;
5044 bool hasPendingExplicitAuto = false;
5045
5046 for (unsigned propertiesParsed = 0; propertiesParsed < 2 && !m_range.atEnd(); ++propertiesParsed) {
5047 if (!propertiesParsed && m_range.peek().id() == CSSValueAuto) {
5048 // 'auto' is a valid value for any of the two longhands, and at this point
5049 // we don't know which one(s) it is meant for. We need to see if there are other values first.
5050 consumeIdent(m_range);
5051 hasPendingExplicitAuto = true;
5052 } else {
5053 if (!columnWidth) {
5054 if ((columnWidth = consumeColumnWidth(m_range)))
5055 continue;
5056 }
5057 if (!columnCount) {
5058 if ((columnCount = consumeColumnCount(m_range)))
5059 continue;
5060 }
5061 // If we didn't find at least one match, this is an invalid shorthand and we have to ignore it.
5062 return false;
5063 }
5064 }
5065
5066 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5067 return false;
5068
5069 // Any unassigned property at this point will become implicit 'auto'.
5070 if (columnWidth)
5071 addProperty(CSSPropertyColumnWidth, CSSPropertyInvalid, columnWidth.releaseNonNull(), important);
5072 else {
5073 addProperty(CSSPropertyColumnWidth, CSSPropertyInvalid, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto), important, !hasPendingExplicitAuto /* implicit */);
5074 hasPendingExplicitAuto = false;
5075 }
5076
5077 if (columnCount)
5078 addProperty(CSSPropertyColumnCount, CSSPropertyInvalid, columnCount.releaseNonNull(), important);
5079 else
5080 addProperty(CSSPropertyColumnCount, CSSPropertyInvalid, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto), important, !hasPendingExplicitAuto /* implicit */);
5081
5082 return true;
5083}
5084
5085bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeShorthandGreedily(const StylePropertyShorthand& shorthand, bool important)
5086{
5087 ASSERT(shorthand.length() <= 6); // Existing shorthands have at most 6 longhands.
5088 RefPtr<CSSValue> longhands[6];
5089 const CSSPropertyID* shorthandProperties = shorthand.properties();
5090 do {
5091 bool foundLonghand = false;
5092 for (size_t i = 0; !foundLonghand && i < shorthand.length(); ++i) {
5093 if (longhands[i])
5094 continue;
5095 longhands[i] = parseSingleValue(shorthandProperties[i], shorthand.id());
5096 if (longhands[i])
5097 foundLonghand = true;
5098 }
5099 if (!foundLonghand)
5100 return false;
5101 } while (!m_range.atEnd());
5102
5103 for (size_t i = 0; i < shorthand.length(); ++i) {
5104 if (longhands[i])
5105 addProperty(shorthandProperties[i], shorthand.id(), longhands[i].releaseNonNull(), important);
5106 else
5107 addProperty(shorthandProperties[i], shorthand.id(), CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue(), important);
5108 }
5109 return true;
5110}
5111
5112bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeFlex(bool important)
5113{
5114 static const double unsetValue = -1;
5115 double flexGrow = unsetValue;
5116 double flexShrink = unsetValue;
5117 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> flexBasis;
5118
5119 if (m_range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone) {
5120 flexGrow = 0;
5121 flexShrink = 0;
5122 flexBasis = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
5123 m_range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
5124 } else {
5125 unsigned index = 0;
5126 while (!m_range.atEnd() && index++ < 3) {
5127 if (auto number = consumeNumberRaw(m_range)) {
5128 if (*number < 0)
5129 return false;
5130 if (flexGrow == unsetValue)
5131 flexGrow = *number;
5132 else if (flexShrink == unsetValue)
5133 flexShrink = *number;
5134 else if (!*number) // flex only allows a basis of 0 (sans units) if flex-grow and flex-shrink values have already been set.
5135 flexBasis = CSSPrimitiveValue::create(0, CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
5136 else
5137 return false;
5138 } else if (!flexBasis) {
5139 if (m_range.peek().id() == CSSValueAuto)
5140 flexBasis = consumeIdent(m_range);
5141 if (!flexBasis)
5142 flexBasis = consumeLengthOrPercent(m_range, m_context.mode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
5143 if (index == 2 && !m_range.atEnd())
5144 return false;
5145 }
5146 }
5147 if (index == 0)
5148 return false;
5149 if (flexGrow == unsetValue)
5150 flexGrow = 1;
5151 if (flexShrink == unsetValue)
5152 flexShrink = 1;
5153
5154 // FIXME: Using % here is a hack to work around intrinsic sizing implementation being
5155 // a mess (e.g., turned off for nested column flexboxes, failing to relayout properly even
5156 // if turned back on for nested columns, etc.). We have layout test coverage of both
5157 // scenarios.
5158 if (!flexBasis)
5159 flexBasis = CSSPrimitiveValue::create(0, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE);
5160 }
5161
5162 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5163 return false;
5164 addProperty(CSSPropertyFlexGrow, CSSPropertyFlex, CSSPrimitiveValue::create(clampTo<float>(flexGrow), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER), important);
5165 addProperty(CSSPropertyFlexShrink, CSSPropertyFlex, CSSPrimitiveValue::create(clampTo<float>(flexShrink), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER), important);
5166 addProperty(CSSPropertyFlexBasis, CSSPropertyFlex, flexBasis.releaseNonNull(), important);
5167 return true;
5168}
5169
5170bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeBorder(RefPtr<CSSValue>& width, RefPtr<CSSValue>& style, RefPtr<CSSValue>& color)
5171{
5172 while (!width || !style || !color) {
5173 if (!width) {
5174 width = consumeLineWidth(m_range, m_context.mode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid);
5175 if (width)
5176 continue;
5177 }
5178 if (!style) {
5179 style = parseSingleValue(CSSPropertyBorderLeftStyle, CSSPropertyBorder);
5180 if (style)
5181 continue;
5182 }
5183 if (!color) {
5184 color = consumeColor(m_range, m_context);
5185 if (color)
5186 continue;
5187 }
5188 break;
5189 }
5190
5191 if (!width && !style && !color)
5192 return false;
5193
5194 if (!width)
5195 width = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5196 if (!style)
5197 style = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5198 if (!color)
5199 color = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5200
5201 return m_range.atEnd();
5202}
5203
5204bool CSSPropertyParser::consume2ValueShorthand(const StylePropertyShorthand& shorthand, bool important)
5205{
5206 ASSERT(shorthand.length() == 2);
5207 const CSSPropertyID* longhands = shorthand.properties();
5208 RefPtr<CSSValue> start = parseSingleValue(longhands[0], shorthand.id());
5209 if (!start)
5210 return false;
5211
5212 RefPtr<CSSValue> end = parseSingleValue(longhands[1], shorthand.id());
5213 bool endImplicit = !end;
5214 if (endImplicit)
5215 end = start;
5216 addProperty(longhands[0], shorthand.id(), start.releaseNonNull(), important);
5217 addProperty(longhands[1], shorthand.id(), end.releaseNonNull(), important, endImplicit);
5218
5219 return m_range.atEnd();
5220}
5221
5222bool CSSPropertyParser::consume4ValueShorthand(const StylePropertyShorthand& shorthand, bool important)
5223{
5224 ASSERT(shorthand.length() == 4);
5225 const CSSPropertyID* longhands = shorthand.properties();
5226 RefPtr<CSSValue> top = parseSingleValue(longhands[0], shorthand.id());
5227 if (!top)
5228 return false;
5229
5230 RefPtr<CSSValue> right = parseSingleValue(longhands[1], shorthand.id());
5231 RefPtr<CSSValue> bottom;
5232 RefPtr<CSSValue> left;
5233 if (right) {
5234 bottom = parseSingleValue(longhands[2], shorthand.id());
5235 if (bottom)
5236 left = parseSingleValue(longhands[3], shorthand.id());
5237 }
5238
5239 bool rightImplicit = !right;
5240 bool bottomImplicit = !bottom;
5241 bool leftImplicit = !left;
5242
5243 if (!right)
5244 right = top;
5245 if (!bottom)
5246 bottom = top;
5247 if (!left)
5248 left = right;
5249
5250 addProperty(longhands[0], shorthand.id(), top.releaseNonNull(), important);
5251 addProperty(longhands[1], shorthand.id(), right.releaseNonNull(), important, rightImplicit);
5252 addProperty(longhands[2], shorthand.id(), bottom.releaseNonNull(), important, bottomImplicit);
5253 addProperty(longhands[3], shorthand.id(), left.releaseNonNull(), important, leftImplicit);
5254
5255 return m_range.atEnd();
5256}
5257
5258bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeBorderImage(CSSPropertyID property, bool important)
5259{
5260 RefPtr<CSSValue> source;
5261 RefPtr<CSSValue> slice;
5262 RefPtr<CSSValue> width;
5263 RefPtr<CSSValue> outset;
5264 RefPtr<CSSValue> repeat;
5265
5266 if (consumeBorderImageComponents(property, m_range, m_context, source, slice, width, outset, repeat)) {
5267 if (!source)
5268 source = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5269 if (!slice)
5270 slice = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5271 if (!width)
5272 width = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5273 if (!outset)
5274 outset = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5275 if (!repeat)
5276 repeat = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5277 switch (property) {
5278 case CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImage:
5279 addProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImageSource, CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImage, source.releaseNonNull(), important);
5280 addProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImageSlice, CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImage, slice.releaseNonNull(), important);
5281 addProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImageWidth, CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImage, width.releaseNonNull(), important);
5282 addProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImageOutset, CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImage, outset.releaseNonNull(), important);
5283 addProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImageRepeat, CSSPropertyWebkitMaskBoxImage, repeat.releaseNonNull(), important);
5284 return true;
5285 case CSSPropertyBorderImage:
5286 addProperty(CSSPropertyBorderImageSource, CSSPropertyBorderImage, source.releaseNonNull(), important);
5287 addProperty(CSSPropertyBorderImageSlice, CSSPropertyBorderImage, slice.releaseNonNull(), important);
5288 addProperty(CSSPropertyBorderImageWidth, CSSPropertyBorderImage, width.releaseNonNull() , important);
5289 addProperty(CSSPropertyBorderImageOutset, CSSPropertyBorderImage, outset.releaseNonNull(), important);
5290 addProperty(CSSPropertyBorderImageRepeat, CSSPropertyBorderImage, repeat.releaseNonNull(), important);
5291 return true;
5292 default:
5293 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
5294 return false;
5295 }
5296 }
5297 return false;
5298}
5299
5300static inline CSSValueID mapFromPageBreakBetween(CSSValueID value)
5301{
5302 if (value == CSSValueAlways)
5303 return CSSValuePage;
5304 if (value == CSSValueAuto || value == CSSValueAvoid || value == CSSValueLeft || value == CSSValueRight)
5305 return value;
5306 return CSSValueInvalid;
5307}
5308
5309static inline CSSValueID mapFromColumnBreakBetween(CSSValueID value)
5310{
5311 if (value == CSSValueAlways)
5312 return CSSValueColumn;
5313 if (value == CSSValueAuto)
5314 return value;
5315 if (value == CSSValueAvoid)
5316 return CSSValueAvoidColumn;
5317 return CSSValueInvalid;
5318}
5319
5320static inline CSSValueID mapFromColumnRegionOrPageBreakInside(CSSValueID value)
5321{
5322 if (value == CSSValueAuto || value == CSSValueAvoid)
5323 return value;
5324 return CSSValueInvalid;
5325}
5326
5327static inline CSSPropertyID mapFromLegacyBreakProperty(CSSPropertyID property)
5328{
5329 if (property == CSSPropertyPageBreakAfter || property == CSSPropertyWebkitColumnBreakAfter)
5330 return CSSPropertyBreakAfter;
5331 if (property == CSSPropertyPageBreakBefore || property == CSSPropertyWebkitColumnBreakBefore)
5332 return CSSPropertyBreakBefore;
5333 ASSERT(property == CSSPropertyPageBreakInside || property == CSSPropertyWebkitColumnBreakInside);
5334 return CSSPropertyBreakInside;
5335}
5336
5337bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeLegacyBreakProperty(CSSPropertyID property, bool important)
5338{
5339 // The fragmentation spec says that page-break-(after|before|inside) are to be treated as
5340 // shorthands for their break-(after|before|inside) counterparts. We'll do the same for the
5341 // non-standard properties -webkit-column-break-(after|before|inside).
5342 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> keyword = consumeIdent(m_range);
5343 if (!keyword)
5344 return false;
5345 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5346 return false;
5347 CSSValueID value = keyword->valueID();
5348 switch (property) {
5349 case CSSPropertyPageBreakAfter:
5350 case CSSPropertyPageBreakBefore:
5351 value = mapFromPageBreakBetween(value);
5352 break;
5353 case CSSPropertyWebkitColumnBreakAfter:
5354 case CSSPropertyWebkitColumnBreakBefore:
5355 value = mapFromColumnBreakBetween(value);
5356 break;
5357 case CSSPropertyPageBreakInside:
5358 case CSSPropertyWebkitColumnBreakInside:
5359 value = mapFromColumnRegionOrPageBreakInside(value);
5360 break;
5361 default:
5362 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
5363 }
5364 if (value == CSSValueInvalid)
5365 return false;
5366
5367 CSSPropertyID genericBreakProperty = mapFromLegacyBreakProperty(property);
5368 addProperty(genericBreakProperty, property, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(value), important);
5369 return true;
5370}
5371
5372static bool consumeBackgroundPosition(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, UnitlessQuirk unitless, RefPtr<CSSValue>& resultX, RefPtr<CSSValue>& resultY)
5373{
5374 do {
5375 auto position = consumePositionCoordinates(range, context.mode, unitless, PositionSyntax::BackgroundPosition);
5376 if (!position)
5377 return false;
5378 addBackgroundValue(resultX, WTFMove(position->x));
5379 addBackgroundValue(resultY, WTFMove(position->y));
5380 } while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(range));
5381 return true;
5382}
5383
5384static bool consumeRepeatStyleComponent(CSSParserTokenRange& range, RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue>& value1, RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue>& value2, bool& implicit)
5385{
5386 if (consumeIdent<CSSValueRepeatX>(range)) {
5387 value1 = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueRepeat);
5388 value2 = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNoRepeat);
5389 implicit = true;
5390 return true;
5391 }
5392 if (consumeIdent<CSSValueRepeatY>(range)) {
5393 value1 = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNoRepeat);
5394 value2 = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueRepeat);
5395 implicit = true;
5396 return true;
5397 }
5398 value1 = consumeIdent<CSSValueRepeat, CSSValueNoRepeat, CSSValueRound, CSSValueSpace>(range);
5399 if (!value1)
5400 return false;
5401
5402 value2 = consumeIdent<CSSValueRepeat, CSSValueNoRepeat, CSSValueRound, CSSValueSpace>(range);
5403 if (!value2) {
5404 value2 = value1;
5405 implicit = true;
5406 }
5407 return true;
5408}
5409
5410static bool consumeRepeatStyle(CSSParserTokenRange& range, RefPtr<CSSValue>& resultX, RefPtr<CSSValue>& resultY, bool& implicit)
5411{
5412 do {
5413 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> repeatX;
5414 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> repeatY;
5415 if (!consumeRepeatStyleComponent(range, repeatX, repeatY, implicit))
5416 return false;
5417 addBackgroundValue(resultX, repeatX.releaseNonNull());
5418 addBackgroundValue(resultY, repeatY.releaseNonNull());
5419 } while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(range));
5420 return true;
5421}
5422
5423// Note: consumeBackgroundShorthand assumes y properties (for example background-position-y) follow
5424// the x properties in the shorthand array.
5425bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeBackgroundShorthand(const StylePropertyShorthand& shorthand, bool important)
5426{
5427 const unsigned longhandCount = shorthand.length();
5428 RefPtr<CSSValue> longhands[10];
5429 ASSERT(longhandCount <= 10);
5430
5431 bool implicit = false;
5432 do {
5433 bool parsedLonghand[10] = { false };
5434 RefPtr<CSSValue> originValue;
5435 do {
5436 bool foundProperty = false;
5437 for (size_t i = 0; i < longhandCount; ++i) {
5438 if (parsedLonghand[i])
5439 continue;
5440
5441 RefPtr<CSSValue> value;
5442 RefPtr<CSSValue> valueY;
5443 CSSPropertyID property = shorthand.properties()[i];
5444 if (property == CSSPropertyBackgroundRepeatX || property == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskRepeatX) {
5445 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> primitiveValue;
5446 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> primitiveValueY;
5447 consumeRepeatStyleComponent(m_range, primitiveValue, primitiveValueY, implicit);
5448 value = primitiveValue;
5449 valueY = primitiveValueY;
5450 } else if (property == CSSPropertyBackgroundPositionX || property == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskPositionX) {
5451 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = m_range;
5452 auto position = consumePositionCoordinates(rangeCopy, m_context.mode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, PositionSyntax::BackgroundPosition);
5453 if (!position)
5454 continue;
5455 value = WTFMove(position->x);
5456 valueY = WTFMove(position->y);
5457 m_range = rangeCopy;
5458 } else if (property == CSSPropertyBackgroundSize || property == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskSize) {
5459 if (!consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range))
5460 continue;
5461 value = consumeBackgroundSize(property, m_range, m_context.mode);
5462 if (!value || !parsedLonghand[i - 1]) // Position must have been parsed in the current layer.
5463 return false;
5464 } else if (property == CSSPropertyBackgroundPositionY || property == CSSPropertyBackgroundRepeatY
5465 || property == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskPositionY || property == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskRepeatY) {
5466 continue;
5467 } else {
5468 value = consumeBackgroundComponent(property, m_range, m_context);
5469 }
5470 if (value) {
5471 if (property == CSSPropertyBackgroundOrigin || property == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskOrigin)
5472 originValue = value;
5473 parsedLonghand[i] = true;
5474 foundProperty = true;
5475 addBackgroundValue(longhands[i], value.releaseNonNull());
5476 if (valueY) {
5477 parsedLonghand[i + 1] = true;
5478 addBackgroundValue(longhands[i + 1], valueY.releaseNonNull());
5479 }
5480 }
5481 }
5482 if (!foundProperty)
5483 return false;
5484 } while (!m_range.atEnd() && m_range.peek().type() != CommaToken);
5485
5486 // FIXME: This will make invalid longhands, see crbug.com/386459
5487 for (size_t i = 0; i < longhandCount; ++i) {
5488 CSSPropertyID property = shorthand.properties()[i];
5489 if (property == CSSPropertyBackgroundColor && !m_range.atEnd()) {
5490 if (parsedLonghand[i])
5491 return false; // Colors are only allowed in the last layer.
5492 continue;
5493 }
5494 if ((property == CSSPropertyBackgroundClip || property == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskClip) && !parsedLonghand[i] && originValue) {
5495 addBackgroundValue(longhands[i], originValue.releaseNonNull());
5496 continue;
5497 }
5498 if (!parsedLonghand[i])
5499 addBackgroundValue(longhands[i], CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue());
5500 }
5501 } while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(m_range));
5502 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5503 return false;
5504
5505 for (size_t i = 0; i < longhandCount; ++i) {
5506 CSSPropertyID property = shorthand.properties()[i];
5507 if (property == CSSPropertyBackgroundSize && longhands[i] && m_context.useLegacyBackgroundSizeShorthandBehavior)
5508 continue;
5509 addProperty(property, shorthand.id(), *longhands[i], important, implicit);
5510 }
5511 return true;
5512}
5513
5514bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeOverflowShorthand(bool important)
5515{
5516 CSSValueID xValueID = m_range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id();
5517 if (!CSSParserFastPaths::isValidKeywordPropertyAndValue(CSSPropertyOverflowY, xValueID, m_context))
5518 return false;
5519
5520 CSSValueID yValueID;
5521 if (m_range.atEnd()) {
5522 yValueID = xValueID;
5523
5524 // FIXME: -webkit-paged-x or -webkit-paged-y only apply to overflow-y. If this value has been
5525 // set using the shorthand, then for now overflow-x will default to auto, but once we implement
5526 // pagination controls, it should default to hidden. If the overflow-y value is anything but
5527 // paged-x or paged-y, then overflow-x and overflow-y should have the same value.
5528 if (xValueID == CSSValueWebkitPagedX || xValueID == CSSValueWebkitPagedY)
5529 xValueID = CSSValueAuto;
5530 } else
5531 yValueID = m_range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id();
5532
5533 if (!CSSParserFastPaths::isValidKeywordPropertyAndValue(CSSPropertyOverflowY, yValueID, m_context))
5534 return false;
5535 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5536 return false;
5537
5538 addProperty(CSSPropertyOverflowX, CSSPropertyOverflow, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(xValueID), important);
5539 addProperty(CSSPropertyOverflowY, CSSPropertyOverflow, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(yValueID), important);
5540 return true;
5541}
5542
5543static bool isCustomIdentValue(const CSSValue& value)
5544{
5545 return is<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value) && downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(value).isCustomIdent();
5546}
5547
5548bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeGridItemPositionShorthand(CSSPropertyID shorthandId, bool important)
5549{
5550 const StylePropertyShorthand& shorthand = shorthandForProperty(shorthandId);
5551 ASSERT(shorthand.length() == 2);
5552 RefPtr<CSSValue> startValue = consumeGridLine(m_range);
5553 if (!startValue)
5554 return false;
5555
5556 RefPtr<CSSValue> endValue;
5557 if (consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range)) {
5558 endValue = consumeGridLine(m_range);
5559 if (!endValue)
5560 return false;
5561 } else {
5562 endValue = isCustomIdentValue(*startValue) ? startValue : CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
5563 }
5564 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5565 return false;
5566 addProperty(shorthand.properties()[0], shorthandId, startValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5567 addProperty(shorthand.properties()[1], shorthandId, endValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5568 return true;
5569}
5570
5571bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeGridAreaShorthand(bool important)
5572{
5573 RefPtr<CSSValue> rowStartValue = consumeGridLine(m_range);
5574 if (!rowStartValue)
5575 return false;
5576 RefPtr<CSSValue> columnStartValue;
5577 RefPtr<CSSValue> rowEndValue;
5578 RefPtr<CSSValue> columnEndValue;
5579 if (consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range)) {
5580 columnStartValue = consumeGridLine(m_range);
5581 if (!columnStartValue)
5582 return false;
5583 if (consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range)) {
5584 rowEndValue = consumeGridLine(m_range);
5585 if (!rowEndValue)
5586 return false;
5587 if (consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range)) {
5588 columnEndValue = consumeGridLine(m_range);
5589 if (!columnEndValue)
5590 return false;
5591 }
5592 }
5593 }
5594 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5595 return false;
5596 if (!columnStartValue)
5597 columnStartValue = isCustomIdentValue(*rowStartValue) ? rowStartValue : CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
5598 if (!rowEndValue)
5599 rowEndValue = isCustomIdentValue(*rowStartValue) ? rowStartValue : CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
5600 if (!columnEndValue)
5601 columnEndValue = isCustomIdentValue(*columnStartValue) ? columnStartValue : CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
5602
5603 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridRowStart, CSSPropertyGridArea, rowStartValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5604 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridColumnStart, CSSPropertyGridArea, columnStartValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5605 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridRowEnd, CSSPropertyGridArea, rowEndValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5606 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridColumnEnd, CSSPropertyGridArea, columnEndValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5607 return true;
5608}
5609
5610bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeGridTemplateRowsAndAreasAndColumns(CSSPropertyID shorthandId, bool important)
5611{
5612 NamedGridAreaMap gridAreaMap;
5613 size_t rowCount = 0;
5614 size_t columnCount = 0;
5615 RefPtr<CSSValueList> templateRows = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
5616
5617 // Persists between loop iterations so we can use the same value for
5618 // consecutive <line-names> values
5619 RefPtr<CSSGridLineNamesValue> lineNames;
5620
5621 do {
5622 // Handle leading <custom-ident>*.
5623 bool hasPreviousLineNames = lineNames;
5624 lineNames = consumeGridLineNames(m_range, lineNames.get());
5625 if (lineNames && !hasPreviousLineNames)
5626 templateRows->append(lineNames.releaseNonNull());
5627
5628 // Handle a template-area's row.
5629 if (m_range.peek().type() != StringToken || !parseGridTemplateAreasRow(m_range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().value(), gridAreaMap, rowCount, columnCount))
5630 return false;
5631 ++rowCount;
5632
5633 // Handle template-rows's track-size.
5634 RefPtr<CSSValue> value = consumeGridTrackSize(m_range, m_context.mode);
5635 if (!value)
5636 value = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
5637 templateRows->append(*value);
5638
5639 // This will handle the trailing/leading <custom-ident>* in the grammar.
5640 lineNames = consumeGridLineNames(m_range);
5641 if (lineNames)
5642 templateRows->append(*lineNames);
5643 } while (!m_range.atEnd() && !(m_range.peek().type() == DelimiterToken && m_range.peek().delimiter() == '/'));
5644
5645 RefPtr<CSSValue> columnsValue;
5646 if (!m_range.atEnd()) {
5647 if (!consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range))
5648 return false;
5649 columnsValue = consumeGridTrackList(m_range, m_context.mode, GridTemplateNoRepeat);
5650 if (!columnsValue || !m_range.atEnd())
5651 return false;
5652 } else {
5653 columnsValue = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
5654 }
5655 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateRows, shorthandId, templateRows.releaseNonNull(), important);
5656 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateColumns, shorthandId, columnsValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5657 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateAreas, shorthandId, CSSGridTemplateAreasValue::create(gridAreaMap, rowCount, columnCount), important);
5658 return true;
5659}
5660
5661bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeGridTemplateShorthand(CSSPropertyID shorthandId, bool important)
5662{
5663 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = m_range;
5664 RefPtr<CSSValue> rowsValue = consumeIdent<CSSValueNone>(m_range);
5665
5666 // 1- 'none' case.
5667 if (rowsValue && m_range.atEnd()) {
5668 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateRows, shorthandId, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone), important);
5669 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateColumns, shorthandId, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone), important);
5670 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateAreas, shorthandId, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone), important);
5671 return true;
5672 }
5673
5674 // 2- <grid-template-rows> / <grid-template-columns>
5675 if (!rowsValue)
5676 rowsValue = consumeGridTrackList(m_range, m_context.mode, GridTemplate);
5677
5678 if (rowsValue) {
5679 if (!consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range))
5680 return false;
5681 RefPtr<CSSValue> columnsValue = consumeGridTemplatesRowsOrColumns(m_range, m_context.mode);
5682 if (!columnsValue || !m_range.atEnd())
5683 return false;
5684
5685 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateRows, shorthandId, rowsValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5686 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateColumns, shorthandId, columnsValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5687 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateAreas, shorthandId, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone), important);
5688 return true;
5689 }
5690
5691 // 3- [ <line-names>? <string> <track-size>? <line-names>? ]+ [ / <track-list> ]?
5692 m_range = rangeCopy;
5693 return consumeGridTemplateRowsAndAreasAndColumns(shorthandId, important);
5694}
5695
5696static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeImplicitGridAutoFlow(CSSParserTokenRange& range, Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue>&& flowDirection)
5697{
5698 // [ auto-flow && dense? ]
5699 if (range.atEnd())
5700 return nullptr;
5701 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
5702 list->append(WTFMove(flowDirection));
5703 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueAutoFlow) {
5704 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
5705 RefPtr<CSSValue> denseIdent = consumeIdent<CSSValueDense>(range);
5706 if (denseIdent)
5707 list->append(denseIdent.releaseNonNull());
5708 } else {
5709 // Dense case
5710 if (range.peek().id() != CSSValueDense)
5711 return nullptr;
5712 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
5713 if (range.atEnd() || range.peek().id() != CSSValueAutoFlow)
5714 return nullptr;
5715 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
5716 list->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueDense));
5717 }
5718
5719 return list;
5720}
5721
5722bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeGridShorthand(bool important)
5723{
5724 ASSERT(shorthandForProperty(CSSPropertyGrid).length() == 6);
5725
5726 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = m_range;
5727
5728 // 1- <grid-template>
5729 if (consumeGridTemplateShorthand(CSSPropertyGrid, important)) {
5730 // It can only be specified the explicit or the implicit grid properties in a single grid declaration.
5731 // The sub-properties not specified are set to their initial value, as normal for shorthands.
5732 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridAutoFlow, CSSPropertyGrid, CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue(), important);
5733 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridAutoColumns, CSSPropertyGrid, CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue(), important);
5734 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridAutoRows, CSSPropertyGrid, CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue(), important);
5735 return true;
5736 }
5737
5738 m_range = rangeCopy;
5739
5740 RefPtr<CSSValue> autoColumnsValue;
5741 RefPtr<CSSValue> autoRowsValue;
5742 RefPtr<CSSValue> templateRows;
5743 RefPtr<CSSValue> templateColumns;
5744 RefPtr<CSSValue> gridAutoFlow;
5745
5746 if (m_range.peek().id() == CSSValueAutoFlow || m_range.peek().id() == CSSValueDense) {
5747 // 2- [ auto-flow && dense? ] <grid-auto-rows>? / <grid-template-columns>
5748 gridAutoFlow = consumeImplicitGridAutoFlow(m_range, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueRow));
5749 if (!gridAutoFlow || m_range.atEnd())
5750 return false;
5751 if (consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range))
5752 autoRowsValue = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5753 else {
5754 autoRowsValue = consumeGridTrackList(m_range, m_context.mode, GridAuto);
5755 if (!autoRowsValue)
5756 return false;
5757 if (!consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range))
5758 return false;
5759 }
5760 if (m_range.atEnd())
5761 return false;
5762 templateColumns = consumeGridTemplatesRowsOrColumns(m_range, m_context.mode);
5763 if (!templateColumns)
5764 return false;
5765 templateRows = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5766 autoColumnsValue = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5767 } else {
5768 // 3- <grid-template-rows> / [ auto-flow && dense? ] <grid-auto-columns>?
5769 templateRows = consumeGridTemplatesRowsOrColumns(m_range, m_context.mode);
5770 if (!templateRows)
5771 return false;
5772 if (!consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(m_range) || m_range.atEnd())
5773 return false;
5774 gridAutoFlow = consumeImplicitGridAutoFlow(m_range, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueColumn));
5775 if (!gridAutoFlow)
5776 return false;
5777 if (m_range.atEnd())
5778 autoColumnsValue = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5779 else {
5780 autoColumnsValue = consumeGridTrackList(m_range, m_context.mode, GridAuto);
5781 if (!autoColumnsValue)
5782 return false;
5783 }
5784 templateColumns = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5785 autoRowsValue = CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue();
5786 }
5787
5788 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5789 return false;
5790
5791 // It can only be specified the explicit or the implicit grid properties in a single grid declaration.
5792 // The sub-properties not specified are set to their initial value, as normal for shorthands.
5793 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateColumns, CSSPropertyGrid, templateColumns.releaseNonNull(), important);
5794 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateRows, CSSPropertyGrid, templateRows.releaseNonNull(), important);
5795 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridTemplateAreas, CSSPropertyGrid, CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue(), important);
5796 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridAutoFlow, CSSPropertyGrid, gridAutoFlow.releaseNonNull(), important);
5797 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridAutoColumns, CSSPropertyGrid, autoColumnsValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5798 addProperty(CSSPropertyGridAutoRows, CSSPropertyGrid, autoRowsValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5799
5800 return true;
5801}
5802
5803bool CSSPropertyParser::consumePlaceContentShorthand(bool important)
5804{
5805 ASSERT(shorthandForProperty(CSSPropertyPlaceContent).length() == 2);
5806
5807 if (m_range.atEnd())
5808 return false;
5809
5810 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = m_range;
5811 bool isBaseline = isBaselineKeyword(m_range.peek().id());
5812 RefPtr<CSSValue> alignContentValue = consumeContentDistributionOverflowPosition(m_range, isContentPositionKeyword);
5813 if (!alignContentValue)
5814 return false;
5815
5816 // justify-content property does not allow the <baseline-position> values.
5817 if (m_range.atEnd() && isBaseline)
5818 return false;
5819 if (isBaselineKeyword(m_range.peek().id()))
5820 return false;
5821
5822 if (m_range.atEnd())
5823 m_range = rangeCopy;
5824 RefPtr<CSSValue> justifyContentValue = consumeContentDistributionOverflowPosition(m_range, isContentPositionOrLeftOrRightKeyword);
5825 if (!justifyContentValue)
5826 return false;
5827 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5828 return false;
5829
5830 addProperty(CSSPropertyAlignContent, CSSPropertyPlaceContent, alignContentValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5831 addProperty(CSSPropertyJustifyContent, CSSPropertyPlaceContent, justifyContentValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5832 return true;
5833}

5838

5840 RefPtr<CSSValue> alignItemsValue = consumeAlignItems(m_range);
5841 if (!alignItemsValue)
5842 return false;
5843
5844 if (m_range.atEnd())
5845 m_range = rangeCopy;
5846 RefPtr<CSSValue> justifyItemsValue = consumeJustifyItems(m_range);
5847 if (!justifyItemsValue)
5848 return false;
5849
5850 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5851 return false;
5852
5853 addProperty(CSSPropertyAlignItems, CSSPropertyPlaceItems, alignItemsValue.releaseNonNull(), important);
5854 addProperty(CSSPropertyJustifyItems, CSSPropertyPlaceItems, justifyItemsValue.releaseNonNull(), important);

5881bool CSSPropertyParser::consumeOverscrollBehaviorShorthand(bool important)
5882{
5883 ASSERT(shorthandForProperty(CSSPropertyOverscrollBehavior).length() == 2);
5884 if (!m_context.overscrollBehaviorEnabled)
5885 return false;
5886
5887 if (m_range.atEnd())
5888 return false;
5889
5890 RefPtr<CSSValue> overscrollBehaviorX = consumeOverscrollBehavior(m_range);
5891 if (!overscrollBehaviorX)
5892 return false;
5893
5894 RefPtr<CSSValue> overscrollBehaviorY;
5895 m_range.consumeWhitespace();
5896 if (m_range.atEnd())
5897 overscrollBehaviorY = overscrollBehaviorX;
5898 else {
5899 overscrollBehaviorY = consumeOverscrollBehavior(m_range);
5900 m_range.consumeWhitespace();
5901 if (!m_range.atEnd())
5902 return false;
5903 }
5904
5905 addProperty(CSSPropertyOverscrollBehaviorX, CSSPropertyOverscrollBehavior, *overscrollBehaviorX, important);
5906 addProperty(CSSPropertyOverscrollBehaviorY, CSSPropertyOverscrollBehavior, *overscrollBehaviorY, important);
5907 return true;
5908}
5909
5910bool CSSPropertyParser::parseShorthand(CSSPropertyID property, bool important)
5911{
5912 switch (property) {
5913 case CSSPropertyWebkitMarginCollapse: {
5914 CSSValueID id = m_range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id();
5915 if (!CSSParserFastPaths::isValidKeywordPropertyAndValue(CSSPropertyWebkitMarginBeforeCollapse, id, m_context))
5916 return false;
5917 addProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitMarginBeforeCollapse, CSSPropertyWebkitMarginCollapse, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(id), important);
5918 if (m_range.atEnd()) {
5919 addProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitMarginAfterCollapse, CSSPropertyWebkitMarginCollapse, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(id), important);
5920 return true;
5921 }
5922 id = m_range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id();
5923 if (!CSSParserFastPaths::isValidKeywordPropertyAndValue(CSSPropertyWebkitMarginAfterCollapse, id, m_context))
5924 return false;
5925 addProperty(CSSPropertyWebkitMarginAfterCollapse, CSSPropertyWebkitMarginCollapse, CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(id), important);
5926 return true;
5927 }
5928 case CSSPropertyOverflow:
5929 return consumeOverflowShorthand(important);
5930 case CSSPropertyOverscrollBehavior:
5931 return consumeOverscrollBehaviorShorthand(important);
5932 case CSSPropertyFont: {
5933 const CSSParserToken& token = m_range.peek();
5934 if (token.id() >= CSSValueCaption && token.id() <= CSSValueStatusBar)
5935 return consumeSystemFont(important);
5936 return consumeFont(important);
5937 }
5938 case CSSPropertyFontVariant:
5939 return consumeFontVariantShorthand(important);
5940 case CSSPropertyBorderSpacing:
5941 return consumeBorderSpacing(important);
5942 case CSSPropertyColumns:
5943 return consumeColumns(important);
5944 case CSSPropertyAnimation:
5945 return consumeAnimationShorthand(animationShorthandForParsing(), important);
5946 case CSSPropertyTransition:
5947 return consumeAnimationShorthand(transitionShorthandForParsing(), important);
5948 case CSSPropertyTextDecoration:
5949 case CSSPropertyWebkitTextDecoration:
5950 // FIXME-NEWPARSER: We need to unprefix -line/-style/-color ASAP and get rid
5951 // of -webkit-text-decoration completely.
5952 return consumeShorthandGreedily(webkitTextDecorationShorthand(), important);
5953 case CSSPropertyInset:
5954 return consume4ValueShorthand(insetShorthand(), important);
5955 case CSSPropertyInsetBlock:
5956 return consume2ValueShorthand(insetBlockShorthand(), important);
5957 case CSSPropertyInsetInline:
5958 return consume2ValueShorthand(insetInlineShorthand(), important);
5959 case CSSPropertyMargin:
5960 return consume4ValueShorthand(marginShorthand(), important);
5961 case CSSPropertyMarginBlock:
5962 return consume2ValueShorthand(marginBlockShorthand(), important);
5963 case CSSPropertyMarginInline:
5964 return consume2ValueShorthand(marginInlineShorthand(), important);
5965 case CSSPropertyPadding:
5966 return consume4ValueShorthand(paddingShorthand(), important);
5967 case CSSPropertyPaddingBlock:
5968 return consume2ValueShorthand(paddingBlockShorthand(), important);
5969 case CSSPropertyPaddingInline:
5970 return consume2ValueShorthand(paddingInlineShorthand(), important);
5971 case CSSPropertyScrollMargin:
5972 return consume4ValueShorthand(scrollMarginShorthand(), important);
5973 case CSSPropertyScrollMarginBlock:
5974 return consume2ValueShorthand(scrollMarginBlockShorthand(), important);
5975 case CSSPropertyScrollMarginInline:
5976 return consume2ValueShorthand(scrollMarginInlineShorthand(), important);
5977 case CSSPropertyScrollPadding:
5978 return consume4ValueShorthand(scrollPaddingShorthand(), important);
5979 case CSSPropertyScrollPaddingBlock:
5980 return consume2ValueShorthand(scrollPaddingBlockShorthand(), important);
5981 case CSSPropertyScrollPaddingInline:
5982 return consume2ValueShorthand(scrollPaddingInlineShorthand(), important);
5983 case CSSPropertyWebkitTextEmphasis:
5984 return consumeShorthandGreedily(webkitTextEmphasisShorthand(), important);
5985 case CSSPropertyOutline:
5986 return consumeShorthandGreedily(outlineShorthand(), important);
5987 case CSSPropertyBorderInline: {
5988 RefPtr<CSSValue> width;
5989 RefPtr<CSSValue> style;
5990 RefPtr<CSSValue> color;
5991 if (!consumeBorder(width, style, color))
5992 return false;
5993
5994 addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyBorderInlineWidth, width.releaseNonNull(), important);
5995 addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyBorderInlineStyle, style.releaseNonNull(), important);
5996 addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyBorderInlineColor, color.releaseNonNull(), important);
5997 return true;
5998 }
5999 case CSSPropertyBorderInlineColor:
6000 return consume2ValueShorthand(borderInlineColorShorthand(), important);
6001 case CSSPropertyBorderInlineStyle:
6002 return consume2ValueShorthand(borderInlineStyleShorthand(), important);
6003 case CSSPropertyBorderInlineWidth:
6004 return consume2ValueShorthand(borderInlineWidthShorthand(), important);
6005 case CSSPropertyBorderInlineStart:
6006 return consumeShorthandGreedily(borderInlineStartShorthand(), important);
6007 case CSSPropertyBorderInlineEnd:
6008 return consumeShorthandGreedily(borderInlineEndShorthand(), important);
6009 case CSSPropertyBorderBlock: {
6010 RefPtr<CSSValue> width;
6011 RefPtr<CSSValue> style;
6012 RefPtr<CSSValue> color;
6013 if (!consumeBorder(width, style, color))
6014 return false;
6015
6016 addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyBorderBlockWidth, width.releaseNonNull(), important);
6017 addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyBorderBlockStyle, style.releaseNonNull(), important);
6018 addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyBorderBlockColor, color.releaseNonNull(), important);
6019 return true;
6020 }
6021 case CSSPropertyBorderBlockColor:
6022 return consume2ValueShorthand(borderBlockColorShorthand(), important);
6023 case CSSPropertyBorderBlockStyle:
6024 return consume2ValueShorthand(borderBlockStyleShorthand(), important);
6025 case CSSPropertyBorderBlockWidth:
6026 return consume2ValueShorthand(borderBlockWidthShorthand(), important);
6027 case CSSPropertyBorderBlockStart:
6028 return consumeShorthandGreedily(borderBlockStartShorthand(), important);
6029 case CSSPropertyBorderBlockEnd:
6030 return consumeShorthandGreedily(borderBlockEndShorthand(), important);
6031 case CSSPropertyWebkitTextStroke:
6032 return consumeShorthandGreedily(webkitTextStrokeShorthand(), important);
6033 case CSSPropertyMarker: {
6034 RefPtr<CSSValue> marker = parseSingleValue(CSSPropertyMarkerStart);
6035 if (!marker || !m_range.atEnd())
6036 return false;
6037 auto markerRef = marker.releaseNonNull();
6038 addProperty(CSSPropertyMarkerStart, CSSPropertyMarker, markerRef.copyRef(), important);
6039 addProperty(CSSPropertyMarkerMid, CSSPropertyMarker, markerRef.copyRef(), important);
6040 addProperty(CSSPropertyMarkerEnd, CSSPropertyMarker, markerRef.copyRef(), important);
6041 return true;
6042 }
6043 case CSSPropertyFlex:
6044 return consumeFlex(important);
6045 case CSSPropertyFlexFlow:
6046 return consumeShorthandGreedily(flexFlowShorthand(), important);
6047 case CSSPropertyColumnRule:
6048 return consumeShorthandGreedily(columnRuleShorthand(), important);
6049 case CSSPropertyListStyle:
6050 return consumeShorthandGreedily(listStyleShorthand(), important);
6051 case CSSPropertyBorderRadius:
6052 case CSSPropertyWebkitBorderRadius: {
6053 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> horizontalRadii[4];
6054 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> verticalRadii[4];
6055 if (!consumeRadii(horizontalRadii, verticalRadii, m_range, m_context.mode, property == CSSPropertyWebkitBorderRadius))
6056 return false;
6057 addProperty(CSSPropertyBorderTopLeftRadius, CSSPropertyBorderRadius, createPrimitiveValuePair(horizontalRadii[0].releaseNonNull(), verticalRadii[0].releaseNonNull(), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce), important);
6058 addProperty(CSSPropertyBorderTopRightRadius, CSSPropertyBorderRadius, createPrimitiveValuePair(horizontalRadii[1].releaseNonNull(), verticalRadii[1].releaseNonNull(), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce), important);
6059 addProperty(CSSPropertyBorderBottomRightRadius, CSSPropertyBorderRadius, createPrimitiveValuePair(horizontalRadii[2].releaseNonNull(), verticalRadii[2].releaseNonNull(), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce), important);
6060 addProperty(CSSPropertyBorderBottomLeftRadius, CSSPropertyBorderRadius, createPrimitiveValuePair(horizontalRadii[3].releaseNonNull(), verticalRadii[3].releaseNonNull(), Pair::IdenticalValueEncoding::Coalesce), important);
6061 return true;
6062 }
6063 case CSSPropertyBorderColor:
6064 return consume4ValueShorthand(borderColorShorthand(), important);
6065 case CSSPropertyBorderStyle:
6066 return consume4ValueShorthand(borderStyleShorthand(), important);
6067 case CSSPropertyBorderWidth:
6068 return consume4ValueShorthand(borderWidthShorthand(), important);
6069 case CSSPropertyBorderTop:
6070 return consumeShorthandGreedily(borderTopShorthand(), important);
6071 case CSSPropertyBorderRight:
6072 return consumeShorthandGreedily(borderRightShorthand(), important);
6073 case CSSPropertyBorderBottom:
6074 return consumeShorthandGreedily(borderBottomShorthand(), important);
6075 case CSSPropertyBorderLeft:
6076 return consumeShorthandGreedily(borderLeftShorthand(), important);
6077 case CSSPropertyBorder: {
6078 RefPtr<CSSValue> width;
6079 RefPtr<CSSValue> style;
6080 RefPtr<CSSValue> color;
6081 if (!consumeBorder(width, style, color))
6082 return false;
6083
6084 addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyBorderWidth, width.releaseNonNull(), important);
6085 addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyBorderStyle, style.releaseNonNull(), important);
6086 addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyBorderColor, color.releaseNonNull(), important);
6087 addExpandedPropertyForValue(CSSPropertyBorderImage, CSSValuePool::singleton().createImplicitInitialValue(), important);
6088 return true;
6089 }
6090 case CSSPropertyBorderImage:
6091 return consumeBorderImage(property, important);
6092 case CSSPropertyPageBreakAfter:
6093 case CSSPropertyPageBreakBefore:
6094 case CSSPropertyPageBreakInside:
6095 case CSSPropertyWebkitColumnBreakAfter:
6096 case CSSPropertyWebkitColumnBreakBefore:
6097 case CSSPropertyWebkitColumnBreakInside:
6098 return consumeLegacyBreakProperty(property, important);
6099 case CSSPropertyWebkitMaskPosition:
6100 case CSSPropertyBackgroundPosition: {
6101 RefPtr<CSSValue> resultX;
6102 RefPtr<CSSValue> resultY;
6103 if (!consumeBackgroundPosition(m_range, m_context, UnitlessQuirk::Allow, resultX, resultY) || !m_range.atEnd())
6104 return false;
6105 addProperty(property == CSSPropertyBackgroundPosition ? CSSPropertyBackgroundPositionX : CSSPropertyWebkitMaskPositionX, property, resultX.releaseNonNull(), important);
6106 addProperty(property == CSSPropertyBackgroundPosition ? CSSPropertyBackgroundPositionY : CSSPropertyWebkitMaskPositionY, property, resultY.releaseNonNull(), important);
6107 return true;
6108 }
6109 case CSSPropertyBackgroundRepeat:
6110 case CSSPropertyWebkitMaskRepeat: {
6111 RefPtr<CSSValue> resultX;
6112 RefPtr<CSSValue> resultY;
6113 bool implicit = false;
6114 if (!consumeRepeatStyle(m_range, resultX, resultY, implicit) || !m_range.atEnd())
6115 return false;
6116 addProperty(property == CSSPropertyBackgroundRepeat ? CSSPropertyBackgroundRepeatX : CSSPropertyWebkitMaskRepeatX, property, resultX.releaseNonNull(), important, implicit);
6117 addProperty(property == CSSPropertyBackgroundRepeat ? CSSPropertyBackgroundRepeatY : CSSPropertyWebkitMaskRepeatY, property, resultY.releaseNonNull(), important, implicit);
6118 return true;
6119 }
6120 case CSSPropertyBackground:
6121 return consumeBackgroundShorthand(backgroundShorthand(), important);
6122 case CSSPropertyWebkitMask:
6123 return consumeBackgroundShorthand(webkitMaskShorthand(), important);
6124 case CSSPropertyTransformOrigin:
6125 return consumeTransformOrigin(important);
6126 case CSSPropertyPerspectiveOrigin:
6127 return consumePerspectiveOrigin(important);
6128 case CSSPropertyGap: {
6129 RefPtr<CSSValue> rowGap = consumeGapLength(m_range, m_context.mode);
6130 RefPtr<CSSValue> columnGap = consumeGapLength(m_range, m_context.mode);
6131 if (!rowGap || !m_range.atEnd())
6132 return false;
6133 if (!columnGap)
6134 columnGap = rowGap;
6135 addProperty(CSSPropertyRowGap, CSSPropertyGap, rowGap.releaseNonNull(), important);
6136 addProperty(CSSPropertyColumnGap, CSSPropertyGap, columnGap.releaseNonNull(), important);
6137 return true;
6138 }
6139 case CSSPropertyGridColumn:
6140 case CSSPropertyGridRow:
6141 return consumeGridItemPositionShorthand(property, important);
6142 case CSSPropertyGridArea:
6143 return consumeGridAreaShorthand(important);
6144 case CSSPropertyGridTemplate:
6145 return consumeGridTemplateShorthand(CSSPropertyGridTemplate, important);
6146 case CSSPropertyGrid:
6147 return consumeGridShorthand(important);
6148 case CSSPropertyPlaceContent:
6149 return consumePlaceContentShorthand(important);
6150 case CSSPropertyPlaceItems:
6151 return consumePlaceItemsShorthand(important);
6152 case CSSPropertyPlaceSelf:
6153 return consumePlaceSelfShorthand(important);
6154 default:
6155 return false;
6156 }
